1
00:01:14,553 --> 00:01:16,171
Do you really want to break up?

2
00:01:16,261 --> 00:01:17,463
I did empty the wardrobe,

3
00:01:17,553 --> 00:01:19,713
did you think I was just
getting them dry cleaned?

4
00:01:19,803 --> 00:01:21,129
We're adults,

5
00:01:21,219 --> 00:01:23,296
you should've just told me directly.

6
00:01:23,386 --> 00:01:24,505
It's exactly because we're adults

7
00:01:24,595 --> 00:01:26,886
that not everything
has to be so direct.

8
00:01:30,886 --> 00:01:34,004
I'm not wealthy
and I'm not very smart,

9
00:01:34,094 --> 00:01:36,171
but I know exactly what I want.

10
00:01:36,261 --> 00:01:37,129
"77 Heartbreaks"

11
00:01:37,219 --> 00:01:38,088
"Heartbeat Shutter"

12
00:01:38,178 --> 00:01:40,796
He's always out drinking
with his friends,

13
00:01:40,886 --> 00:01:42,511
and he's a reckless driver.

14
00:01:42,762 --> 00:01:44,463
How can I not worry about him?

15
00:01:44,553 --> 00:01:47,843
I know, is it so hard
to make a phone call or send a text?

16
00:01:51,094 --> 00:01:53,129
Eva's father had a wish,

17
00:01:53,219 --> 00:01:55,088
which is for his daughter
to find a good husband.

18
00:01:55,178 --> 00:01:57,672
Mrs Lui, I did think about marriage.

19
00:01:57,762 --> 00:01:59,261
The happiness I'll give you

20
00:01:59,843 --> 00:02:02,630
will definitely make up
the 77 times I broke your heart.

21
00:02:02,720 --> 00:02:04,886
I hope you can forgive me
one last time.

22
00:02:07,344 --> 00:02:10,261
You'd already closed the file,
yet here you are again.

23
00:02:10,595 --> 00:02:12,094
You're just torturing yourself.

24
00:02:13,053 --> 00:02:14,754
I left that notebook out on purpose

25
00:02:14,844 --> 00:02:15,753
for you to see,

26
00:02:15,843 --> 00:02:16,879
and I guess this is what

27
00:02:16,969 --> 00:02:19,428
that girl left out on purpose
for me too.

28
00:02:19,720 --> 00:02:20,803
Look...

29
00:02:21,428 --> 00:02:23,171
I was in a mess, I don't have...

30
00:02:23,261 --> 00:02:24,588
Leave me alone!

31
00:02:24,678 --> 00:02:25,672
"77 Heartbreaks"

32
00:02:52,636 --> 00:02:53,630
That's a definite no.

33
00:02:56,927 --> 00:02:58,886
- You look gorgeous!
- How's this one?

34
00:03:00,261 --> 00:03:01,843
No way!

35
00:03:02,094 --> 00:03:03,088
So ugly.

36
00:03:05,636 --> 00:03:06,927
Cheers!

37
00:03:07,927 --> 00:03:08,921
It's too tight.

38
00:03:14,261 --> 00:03:15,595
One, two, three!

39
00:03:37,219 --> 00:03:38,927
"77 Heartwarmings"

40
00:03:42,762 --> 00:03:44,219
Solicitor Eva Lui!

41
00:03:45,720 --> 00:03:47,213
Are you ready to go?

42
00:03:47,303 --> 00:03:50,796
White already comes with
so many styles, it's hard to pick.

43
00:03:50,886 --> 00:03:54,171
Men are no different,
they come in all shapes and sizes.

44
00:03:54,261 --> 00:03:56,844
- Afraid of picking the wrong one?
- No.

45
00:03:58,094 --> 00:03:59,546
I'm not ready.

46
00:03:59,636 --> 00:04:01,796
You're usually so decisive,

47
00:04:01,886 --> 00:04:03,672
but now you're just
throwing out excuses.

48
00:04:03,762 --> 00:04:06,296
If you do pick the wrong one,
just get a divorce.

49
00:04:06,386 --> 00:04:09,380
I'm moving heaven and earth
to put together this wedding

50
00:04:09,470 --> 00:04:10,886
just so I can get divorced?

51
00:04:11,011 --> 00:04:11,837
According to statistics,

52
00:04:11,927 --> 00:04:15,338
11.61 million marriages were
registered nationwide last year.

53
00:04:15,428 --> 00:04:19,421
Meanwhile,
there were 2.32 million divorces

54
00:04:19,511 --> 00:04:22,588
and a 20 percent increase
in divorce rate.

55
00:04:22,678 --> 00:04:25,380
Which also means one out of five
marriages end in divorce,

56
00:04:25,470 --> 00:04:29,546
and there is another divorce
happening every three minutes.

57
00:04:29,636 --> 00:04:32,796
Based on the cases
our firm has handled,

58
00:04:32,886 --> 00:04:34,505
these are the top ten reasons
for divorce.

59
00:04:34,595 --> 00:04:36,796
He doesn't love me anymore.

60
00:04:36,886 --> 00:04:38,672
That's right,
I don't love her anymore.

61
00:04:38,762 --> 00:04:41,178
We haven't talked in over 40 years.

62
00:04:41,886 --> 00:04:46,254
He never gave me a cent
to raise these kids.

63
00:04:46,344 --> 00:04:48,843
- Don't play with that.
- Isn't he useless?

64
00:04:49,261 --> 00:04:51,094
An irresponsible,
useless piece of trash!

65
00:04:51,678 --> 00:04:56,129
I won't get alimony
if I don't get divorced,

66
00:04:56,219 --> 00:04:59,837
and how will I have
a steady income then?

67
00:04:59,927 --> 00:05:01,254
Let me tell you, lady.

68
00:05:01,344 --> 00:05:03,380
A family unit can only
buy one home in China.

69
00:05:03,470 --> 00:05:06,254
Baby, if we're both single,

70
00:05:06,344 --> 00:05:08,213
then we can buy another home!

71
00:05:08,303 --> 00:05:09,754
So we can each have one!

72
00:05:09,844 --> 00:05:13,754
She's changed,
she used to be thinner than me!

73
00:05:13,844 --> 00:05:15,927
- She abuses me.
- Shut your mouth!

74
00:05:16,053 --> 00:05:17,505
No sex!

75
00:05:17,595 --> 00:05:20,171
I don't know why we got married...

76
00:05:20,261 --> 00:05:22,213
In the past year, our firm's offices

77
00:05:22,303 --> 00:05:25,046
in Hong Kong, Guangzhou and Shenzhen

78
00:05:25,136 --> 00:05:26,630
saw business double.

79
00:05:26,720 --> 00:05:30,053
However, this is also
the tragedy of our generation.

80
00:05:38,511 --> 00:05:40,463
"Adam Cheung"

81
00:05:40,553 --> 00:05:44,595
"We held hands for the first time
8 years ago."

82
00:05:47,011 --> 00:05:48,005
Come in.

83
00:05:48,803 --> 00:05:50,713
Daisy says when you get
to the airport in London,

84
00:05:50,803 --> 00:05:52,672
there will be a driver
waiting for you.

85
00:05:52,762 --> 00:05:54,213
She's truly a winner at life,

86
00:05:54,303 --> 00:05:57,046
even her kid's one-month banquet
has to go international.

87
00:05:57,136 --> 00:05:59,338
Why don't you fly out early
with me anyway?

88
00:05:59,428 --> 00:06:00,296
Oh, I know.

89
00:06:00,386 --> 00:06:03,004
You don't want to be on
the same plane as NT Tang, right?

90
00:06:03,094 --> 00:06:04,004
Hi, Mr Tang.

91
00:06:04,094 --> 00:06:05,261
I'm Eva.

92
00:06:05,803 --> 00:06:08,470
Hi there, you can just call me NT.

93
00:06:10,595 --> 00:06:13,380
He's already pretty nice
for a nouveau riche.

94
00:06:13,470 --> 00:06:15,927
Plenty of girls would jump
at the chance of marrying him,

95
00:06:16,053 --> 00:06:17,453
and you would've been set for life.

96
00:06:17,803 --> 00:06:18,843
What are you doing?

97
00:06:20,553 --> 00:06:22,505
Even your phone still misses Adam?

98
00:06:22,595 --> 00:06:24,428
You guys have split
for a year already.

99
00:06:25,094 --> 00:06:26,463
"Saving"

100
00:06:26,553 --> 00:06:28,720
Good thing that
you back-up the phone regularly.

101
00:06:37,344 --> 00:06:39,053
Be yourself, be happy!

102
00:06:41,261 --> 00:06:43,672
Be yourself, be happy?

103
00:06:43,762 --> 00:06:45,303
I wish too.

104
00:06:45,843 --> 00:06:48,720
Be happy...

105
00:06:48,844 --> 00:06:51,088
Excuse me, it's time to close.

106
00:06:51,178 --> 00:06:52,219
Sorry.

107
00:07:05,136 --> 00:07:06,129
Miss.

108
00:07:06,219 --> 00:07:07,630
In lightning speed,

109
00:07:07,720 --> 00:07:09,754
we've transferred your phone's data.

110
00:07:09,844 --> 00:07:10,838
Take a look.

111
00:07:14,344 --> 00:07:15,296
How do I unlock it?

112
00:07:15,386 --> 00:07:19,553
The factory setting for this phone
is like the M shape,

113
00:07:20,094 --> 00:07:21,672
just make an "M" to unlock it.

114
00:07:21,762 --> 00:07:22,753
If you have anything
against the word,

115
00:07:22,843 --> 00:07:24,046
you may as well change it
when you get home.

116
00:07:24,136 --> 00:07:26,261
Go online and see if it works now.

117
00:07:27,844 --> 00:07:29,088
Perfect, all done.

118
00:07:29,178 --> 00:07:30,588
"Why are you still single?"

119
00:07:30,678 --> 00:07:32,636
Why are you still single?

120
00:07:38,094 --> 00:07:40,171
Because I love myself the most.

121
00:07:40,261 --> 00:07:43,505
I overthink things
and it's hard to love someone new.

122
00:07:43,595 --> 00:07:46,630
Because I can't handle
another betrayal.

123
00:07:46,720 --> 00:07:49,546
Because I don't want to
sacrifice so much for someone else.

124
00:07:49,636 --> 00:07:51,178
Freedom!

125
00:07:57,886 --> 00:08:00,178
- Another bottle, handsome?
- Thanks.

126
00:08:04,636 --> 00:08:05,713
"Adam Cheung"

127
00:08:05,803 --> 00:08:07,643
"We held hands for the first time
8 years ago."

128
00:08:07,843 --> 00:08:09,505
I'll treat your mother better,

129
00:08:09,595 --> 00:08:12,254
I won't drive drunk and buying
those raisin cookies anymore.

130
00:08:12,344 --> 00:08:13,588
All the mistakes
I made in that book,

131
00:08:13,678 --> 00:08:14,546
I'll never make them again.

132
00:08:14,636 --> 00:08:15,762
Believe me.

133
00:08:16,762 --> 00:08:19,129
Once, I had the love of a lifetime,

134
00:08:19,219 --> 00:08:21,879
- but I didn't treasure it!
- Oh, forget it.

135
00:08:21,969 --> 00:08:23,505
You guys broke up a year ago,

136
00:08:23,595 --> 00:08:26,588
you don't have to
act brokenhearted forever, right?

137
00:08:26,678 --> 00:08:30,213
Right now, you ought to be happy.

138
00:08:30,303 --> 00:08:33,753
You've just escaped
a maximum security prison.

139
00:08:33,843 --> 00:08:35,713
Just because of leaving
a bottle of beer behind,

140
00:08:35,803 --> 00:08:38,053
you don't have to go back
in the cell for it, dummy!

141
00:08:39,762 --> 00:08:40,843
One of this, please.

142
00:08:41,553 --> 00:08:43,636
- Me, too.
- Thank you.

143
00:08:44,844 --> 00:08:46,004
Where's Francis?

144
00:08:46,094 --> 00:08:47,630
I guess his wife
didn't grant him a release then.

145
00:08:47,720 --> 00:08:49,129
You have to understand,

146
00:08:49,219 --> 00:08:51,754
having the freedom to watch football
is some kind of bliss.

147
00:08:51,844 --> 00:08:53,505
We used to be happy, too.

148
00:08:53,595 --> 00:08:55,380
When we watched games at his place,

149
00:08:55,470 --> 00:08:58,213
Eva used to take such good
care of us and served us drinks.

150
00:08:58,303 --> 00:08:59,463
She even made us instant noodles
whenever we are hungry,

151
00:08:59,553 --> 00:09:01,213
and no to mention
that crispy chicken!

152
00:09:01,303 --> 00:09:02,672
So delicious!

153
00:09:02,762 --> 00:09:05,630
As if to have a friend
with a girlfriend

154
00:09:05,720 --> 00:09:06,713
that can cook as well as her,

155
00:09:06,803 --> 00:09:07,672
do you know how hard it is?

156
00:09:07,762 --> 00:09:12,927
Look, we're here to watch football
and other ball-shaped objects.

157
00:09:15,553 --> 00:09:16,754
What a ball game!

158
00:09:16,844 --> 00:09:17,837
- Thanks, guys.
- You're the real winner.

159
00:09:17,927 --> 00:09:19,094
Such a nice ball game.

160
00:09:20,053 --> 00:09:23,380
- You didn't even take a peek?
- They were spilling out.

161
00:09:23,470 --> 00:09:25,636
- You can keep them.
- Sure.

162
00:09:26,927 --> 00:09:28,470
You pulled a prison break?

163
00:09:28,720 --> 00:09:31,338
No, my wife and her mother
are away visiting family.

164
00:09:31,428 --> 00:09:32,879
Good thing that
I didn't have to go with them.

165
00:09:32,969 --> 00:09:34,254
So once I dropped them
off at the airport,

166
00:09:34,344 --> 00:09:36,171
I came straight here
to see you rascals.

167
00:09:36,261 --> 00:09:37,672
It's really been a while, rascal.

168
00:09:37,762 --> 00:09:38,672
Yeah.

169
00:09:38,762 --> 00:09:41,505
The last time I saw you,
you were just a little fat.

170
00:09:41,595 --> 00:09:43,837
- Now you've really blown up.
- Get off, man.

171
00:09:43,927 --> 00:09:45,753
Dude, you just wanted a girl, right?

172
00:09:45,843 --> 00:09:47,046
Why did you get married?

173
00:09:47,136 --> 00:09:48,713
There are so many dating apps
out there.

174
00:09:48,803 --> 00:09:49,630
What I mean is,

175
00:09:49,720 --> 00:09:51,796
you can't give up
all the functions on your phone

176
00:09:51,886 --> 00:09:53,505
for a single app.

177
00:09:53,595 --> 00:09:55,380
But I really do love my wife,

178
00:09:55,470 --> 00:09:57,296
and I gained weight
because I'm happy.

179
00:09:57,386 --> 00:09:59,595
And I enjoy being ordered around,
what do you care?

180
00:10:00,678 --> 00:10:02,843
Second half's starting soon,
so shut up.

181
00:10:04,136 --> 00:10:05,720
We've already lost
in the first half.

182
00:10:06,344 --> 00:10:08,837
They'll catch up in the second half,

183
00:10:08,927 --> 00:10:10,837
that's what makes the game
so exciting, right?

184
00:10:10,927 --> 00:10:13,296
He lost 77-0 to Eva
in the first half.

185
00:10:13,386 --> 00:10:15,470
- You try catching up!
- Come on.

186
00:10:16,136 --> 00:10:17,338
It's your fault
for getting caught red-handed.

187
00:10:17,428 --> 00:10:19,213
The very night
you split up with Eva,

188
00:10:19,303 --> 00:10:20,171
you brought a girl home.

189
00:10:20,261 --> 00:10:21,753
- You deserved what you got.
- I don't agree.

190
00:10:21,843 --> 00:10:22,796
He was drunk,

191
00:10:22,886 --> 00:10:25,672
and he was technically broken up
with Eva at the time.

192
00:10:25,762 --> 00:10:31,296
Girls always expect you to go
through a mourning period like them.

193
00:10:31,386 --> 00:10:33,463
If you bring a girl home
within the first 7 days,

194
00:10:33,553 --> 00:10:35,136
you're disrespecting the dead!

195
00:10:36,762 --> 00:10:38,254
Drink up and shut up.

196
00:10:38,344 --> 00:10:39,879
Drink up, you two.

197
00:10:39,969 --> 00:10:40,963
You're talking too much.

198
00:10:41,969 --> 00:10:44,505
You know, I use an apology app
on my wife all the time.

199
00:10:44,595 --> 00:10:45,803
You should take a look.

200
00:10:47,843 --> 00:10:48,837
That's absurd!

201
00:11:21,636 --> 00:11:22,927
Mom, I'm back.

202
00:11:23,886 --> 00:11:25,011
Welcome home.

203
00:11:28,136 --> 00:11:29,088
How are you feeling today?

204
00:11:29,178 --> 00:11:30,386
Is your stomach better?

205
00:11:32,261 --> 00:11:33,837
What about you?

206
00:11:33,927 --> 00:11:36,511
You can't skip your medication.

207
00:11:37,803 --> 00:11:40,969
Those pills are making me drowsy
all the time.

208
00:11:42,428 --> 00:11:44,178
What have we done to deserve this?

209
00:11:44,886 --> 00:11:48,219
Me with the depression
and you with the stomach problem.

210
00:11:50,843 --> 00:11:52,129
You really should move,

211
00:11:52,219 --> 00:11:53,753
and live in
a more comfortable place.

212
00:11:53,843 --> 00:11:56,843
What for? This is my home.

213
00:11:57,927 --> 00:12:00,553
Some tasks are a little hard
without a man around, that's all.

214
00:12:03,011 --> 00:12:05,011
Everyone uses those
T5 energy conserving bulbs now,

215
00:12:05,428 --> 00:12:07,879
these fluorescent lights
are old and hard to buy.

216
00:12:07,969 --> 00:12:13,011
I asked your dad to change them,
but he refused to.

217
00:12:14,094 --> 00:12:15,178
Got it.

218
00:12:16,511 --> 00:12:19,796
Mom, dad's been gone for so long.

219
00:12:19,886 --> 00:12:21,963
If you need to cry,
you can do it in the living room.

220
00:12:22,053 --> 00:12:24,171
It's so stuffy in the kitchen,

221
00:12:24,261 --> 00:12:26,505
women don't have to
suffer like this anymore.

222
00:12:26,595 --> 00:12:28,463
I'm not suffering.

223
00:12:28,553 --> 00:12:30,011
I told you,

224
00:12:30,803 --> 00:12:34,921
I may have married the wrong man,
but I had the right daughter.

225
00:12:35,011 --> 00:12:38,713
But you've devoted your whole life
to your husband and daughter,

226
00:12:38,803 --> 00:12:41,927
you ought to do something
for yourself and be happy.

227
00:12:42,886 --> 00:12:44,595
I'm happy if you're happy.

228
00:12:49,762 --> 00:12:52,380
By the way, I'm going
to the UK and see Daisy tomorrow.

229
00:12:52,470 --> 00:12:53,837
I won't be around
to take care of you,

230
00:12:53,927 --> 00:12:55,428
so you should call up your friends.

231
00:12:57,927 --> 00:13:01,171
I don't need friends,
they're so annoying.

232
00:13:01,261 --> 00:13:03,011
There's bound to be an exception.

233
00:13:05,386 --> 00:13:07,803
Well, there's one.

234
00:13:09,969 --> 00:13:11,762
But I haven't seen him in decades,

235
00:13:12,261 --> 00:13:13,963
and I don't even have his number.

236
00:13:14,053 --> 00:13:16,296
It's easy
to find someone these days,

237
00:13:16,386 --> 00:13:18,088
give me the name
and I'll find him for you.

238
00:13:18,178 --> 00:13:19,713
It's that easy?

239
00:13:19,803 --> 00:13:21,094
His name is Tsang Po-wah.

240
00:13:21,595 --> 00:13:23,470
Tsang Po-wah?

241
00:13:24,053 --> 00:13:24,969
Well, never mind.

242
00:13:25,094 --> 00:13:28,428
It's been decades, I don't even know
if he's still alive.

243
00:13:29,927 --> 00:13:31,338
Remember to bring
your stomach medicine.

244
00:13:31,428 --> 00:13:33,338
Alright, I got it.

245
00:13:33,428 --> 00:13:35,053
Need anything from the UK?

246
00:13:36,219 --> 00:13:38,636
I have to spend
my money somewhere...

247
00:13:44,053 --> 00:13:46,094
"Sorry App"

248
00:13:59,011 --> 00:14:00,428
I'm sorry, Eva.

249
00:14:07,178 --> 00:14:08,511
I'm sorry, Eva.

250
00:14:11,843 --> 00:14:12,837
This is so stupid!

251
00:14:51,844 --> 00:14:52,753
Let's go that way.

252
00:14:52,843 --> 00:14:55,713
We're trying to find our way,
this isn't a maze.

253
00:14:55,803 --> 00:14:58,178
- You can't just guess a way out.
- Let's just go!

254
00:15:21,886 --> 00:15:24,428
Let me help you,
or you'll hurt your hip again.

255
00:15:27,303 --> 00:15:29,969
Did you bring your passport?
You know how forgetful you are.

256
00:15:31,011 --> 00:15:32,843
Of course I did.

257
00:15:35,053 --> 00:15:36,047
Wait, no way!

258
00:15:36,178 --> 00:15:38,421
I told you, you're always like this.

259
