295
00:18:31,178 --> 00:18:32,886
Yours, Melody.

296
00:18:48,094 --> 00:18:49,136
Thank you.

297
00:18:51,178 --> 00:18:53,511
I didn't know girls still do
knitting these days.

298
00:18:55,428 --> 00:18:57,595
This is for a special person.

299
00:18:58,219 --> 00:18:59,344
A special one?

300
00:19:00,803 --> 00:19:02,754
Oh, for your kid, right?

301
00:19:02,844 --> 00:19:04,338
No...

302
00:19:04,428 --> 00:19:06,094
For my friend's kid.

303
00:19:07,053 --> 00:19:09,129
You must be very patient

304
00:19:09,219 --> 00:19:12,011
Kind and old school.

305
00:19:13,470 --> 00:19:18,421
You must be very neat
and sentimental.

306
00:19:18,511 --> 00:19:20,136
Me? Sentimental?

307
00:19:20,969 --> 00:19:23,844
You look sad
holding the paper heart over there.

308
00:19:24,886 --> 00:19:26,844
You mean the origami?

309
00:19:28,178 --> 00:19:30,963
I shouldn't say this,
but you look familiar.

310
00:19:31,053 --> 00:19:33,171
Sir, flight HW77.

311
00:19:33,261 --> 00:19:34,338
Last call for boarding.

312
00:19:34,428 --> 00:19:36,678
- Oh, I gotta go.
- Thank you.

313
00:19:42,219 --> 00:19:44,219
Oh, my phone.

314
00:19:49,720 --> 00:19:51,136
Bye...

315
00:19:51,386 --> 00:19:52,428
Thank you very much.

316
00:20:13,553 --> 00:20:16,178
- Mrs Lui.
- They're writing parking tickets.

317
00:20:18,678 --> 00:20:19,672
It's okay.

318
00:20:24,428 --> 00:20:26,428
I've seen your car around
a few times.

319
00:20:26,927 --> 00:20:29,463
I really don't get
how you young people think.

320
00:20:29,553 --> 00:20:32,879
Once you lose touch with someone
back then, it was for good.

321
00:20:32,969 --> 00:20:34,213
But it's so easy to find people now,

322
00:20:34,303 --> 00:20:37,386
you can just make a call
or find them on the internet.

323
00:20:38,803 --> 00:20:41,053
This is useless
to sit around doing nothing.

324
00:20:43,303 --> 00:20:44,297
Mrs Lui!

325
00:20:45,094 --> 00:20:46,088
Mrs Lui!

326
00:20:51,720 --> 00:20:54,844
"Eva's phone"

327
00:21:04,094 --> 00:21:05,088
Hello.

328
00:21:34,303 --> 00:21:35,386
What's going on?

329
00:21:36,178 --> 00:21:37,762
Everything's in Thai.

330
00:21:40,511 --> 00:21:41,553
My phone.

331
00:21:45,762 --> 00:21:47,011
Bye...

332
00:21:47,844 --> 00:21:48,838
Thank you very much.

333
00:21:52,511 --> 00:21:53,595
No way...

334
00:21:56,470 --> 00:21:57,296
Eva.

335
00:21:57,386 --> 00:21:58,753
Do you know what today is?

336
00:21:58,843 --> 00:22:00,421
It's not the anniversary
of our first meeting,

337
00:22:00,511 --> 00:22:02,505
nor the anniversary
of the first time we held hands.

338
00:22:02,595 --> 00:22:04,296
It's the first anniversary
of our breakup.

339
00:22:04,386 --> 00:22:05,254
In the past year,

340
00:22:05,344 --> 00:22:08,094
I keep feeling
like I've lost something...

341
00:22:21,844 --> 00:22:25,470
"Happy 100 days"

342
00:22:34,969 --> 00:22:36,136
This is for you.

343
00:22:36,595 --> 00:22:38,219
This is lovely, did you knit this?

344
00:22:39,428 --> 00:22:40,630
That's so thoughtful.

345
00:22:40,720 --> 00:22:42,546
It's not like people
who is giving gold accessories

346
00:22:42,636 --> 00:22:43,796
that I don't even know
what I'm supposed to do with them!

347
00:22:43,886 --> 00:22:45,505
- Hi, ladies.
- It's beauitful...

348
00:22:45,595 --> 00:22:46,796
- Hi, baby...
- Hi...

349
00:22:46,886 --> 00:22:48,254
Do you mind if I steal the princess?

350
00:22:48,344 --> 00:22:49,171
- Hi.
- Of course, that's a good idea.

351
00:22:49,261 --> 00:22:51,129
- Is that alright?
- Let daddy have our little princess.

352
00:22:51,219 --> 00:22:52,344
Yeah, thank you.

353
00:22:52,844 --> 00:22:54,421
- Hi, sweetheart.
- Go to daddy.

354
00:22:54,511 --> 00:22:55,713
- Bye.
- Thanks, daddy.

355
00:22:55,803 --> 00:22:56,797
Bye, Daisy.

356
00:22:57,927 --> 00:22:59,837
I'm amazed that
you had the time to knit the hat.

357
00:22:59,927 --> 00:23:02,004
The baby's head is so small,
I got it done on the plane.

358
00:23:02,094 --> 00:23:02,963
So?

359
00:23:03,053 --> 00:23:04,421
Have you located my phone yet?

360
00:23:04,511 --> 00:23:05,754
Not yet.

361
00:23:05,844 --> 00:23:08,879
If your phone is off,
there's no way to track it.

362
00:23:08,969 --> 00:23:10,678
Maybe he's still on the plane.

363
00:23:11,386 --> 00:23:13,843
- What should I do?
- How did you mess that up?

364
00:23:14,011 --> 00:23:16,796
How did you switch your phone
with a Thai guy anyway?

365
00:23:16,886 --> 00:23:19,921
So I guess you can call this
a "Tom Yum Phone"!

366
00:23:20,011 --> 00:23:21,296
That's a terrible joke.

367
00:23:21,386 --> 00:23:24,753
Was he trying to steal your phone
or steal your heart?

368
00:23:24,843 --> 00:23:26,763
- What are you talking about?
- Steal your heart.

369
00:23:27,094 --> 00:23:29,837
Hey, look at this.
These photos are pretty cool.

370
00:23:29,927 --> 00:23:31,386
- Let me see.
- What's that?

371
00:23:31,636 --> 00:23:33,844
- That looks familiar.
- Is that's the Star Ferry Pier?

372
00:23:37,843 --> 00:23:40,843
- Oh, "A Brokenhearted Dolphin".
- How do you know?

373
00:23:43,969 --> 00:23:49,886
And this is "Lazy Afternoon",
that's the name of the piece.

374
00:23:51,843 --> 00:23:56,094
The guy who made this
is named the Space-time Intruder.

375
00:23:56,511 --> 00:24:00,713
Even to this day,
no one knows who he is.

376
00:24:00,803 --> 00:24:03,338
But he's already intruded
over 35 cities

377
00:24:03,428 --> 00:24:05,338
and left 890 intruder pieces.

378
00:24:05,428 --> 00:24:07,386
There are 75 in Hong Kong alone.

379
00:24:08,219 --> 00:24:09,837
How did you not know this?

380
00:24:09,927 --> 00:24:10,921
I don't care who he is.

381
00:24:11,011 --> 00:24:13,046
Putting stickers
on buildings like that

382
00:24:13,136 --> 00:24:14,546
is against the law.

383
00:24:14,636 --> 00:24:15,879
He's only in trouble
if he gets caught,

384
00:24:15,969 --> 00:24:18,178
and who is just conquered Central
last week.

385
00:24:18,843 --> 00:24:22,046
Maybe the phone doesn't actually
belong to that Intruder guy,

386
00:24:22,136 --> 00:24:23,463
but just a fan of him instead?

387
00:24:23,553 --> 00:24:24,421
It doesn't matter.

388
00:24:24,511 --> 00:24:26,046
If he's handsome,

389
00:24:26,136 --> 00:24:28,136
then this is awfully romantic!

390
00:24:28,553 --> 00:24:29,421
Think about it.

391
00:24:29,511 --> 00:24:32,753
The same phone model
with the same pattern lock.

392
00:24:32,843 --> 00:24:33,672
It's fate.

393
00:24:33,762 --> 00:24:36,129
That's fate, I totally agree.

394
00:24:36,219 --> 00:24:37,254
I've looked into this.

395
00:24:37,344 --> 00:24:38,963
Of all lock patterns on this phone,

396
00:24:39,053 --> 00:24:41,505
there are 389,112 possible ways.

397
00:24:41,595 --> 00:24:44,344
For two people to have
the exact same lock pattern,

398
00:24:44,803 --> 00:24:45,879
this is just destiny.

399
00:24:45,969 --> 00:24:48,505
The lock pattern
was the factory setting,

400
00:24:48,595 --> 00:24:50,254
and the very destiny
that you're talking about

401
00:24:50,344 --> 00:24:52,464
only happened because
I didn't have time to change it.

402
00:24:54,219 --> 00:24:56,129
I have an idea.

403
00:24:56,219 --> 00:24:57,754
Why don't we check on the messages

404
00:24:57,844 --> 00:25:00,046
of this Tom Yum Phone?

405
00:25:00,136 --> 00:25:02,380
No way, it's an invasion of privacy.

406
00:25:02,470 --> 00:25:03,380
Sorry, ladies.

407
00:25:03,470 --> 00:25:05,754
I think our little baby
just made a mess,

408
00:25:05,844 --> 00:25:06,753
could you give me a hand?

409
00:25:06,843 --> 00:25:07,843
I have to go upstairs.

410
00:25:08,344 --> 00:25:09,511
- Sorry.
- See you later.

411
00:25:17,178 --> 00:25:19,053
Hello, Eva!

412
00:25:22,219 --> 00:25:24,053
I'm fine, thank you.

413
00:25:24,470 --> 00:25:26,428
She didn't say "How are you?"

414
00:25:27,053 --> 00:25:30,046
It's been four whole seasons
since we last met,

415
00:25:30,136 --> 00:25:31,754
I'm sure that
you've missed me very much.

416
00:25:31,844 --> 00:25:32,927
Excuse me.

417
00:25:34,927 --> 00:25:36,046
I'll wait here for you.

418
00:25:36,136 --> 00:25:39,338
- Why are you calling my phone?
- Hello.

419
00:25:39,428 --> 00:25:41,753
- Eva, Adam is looking for you.
- Hello?

420
00:25:41,843 --> 00:25:43,837
- Ask him what he wants.
- She'd like to know what you want.

421
00:25:43,927 --> 00:25:44,921
Hello, what is it?

422
00:25:46,511 --> 00:25:47,843
What's the matter with you guys?

423
00:25:48,219 --> 00:25:49,296
The Thai guy called,

424
00:25:49,386 --> 00:25:51,713
and says he can go to Hong Kong
to switch the phones back.

425
00:25:51,803 --> 00:25:52,927
Really? When?

426
00:25:53,261 --> 00:25:55,713
He didn't mention about it,
but he said he'll call again.

427
00:25:55,803 --> 00:25:58,053
Eva, Adam says
that your mother's in the hospital.

428
00:26:00,303 --> 00:26:02,553
Okay, thank you.

429
00:26:04,011 --> 00:26:06,963
You won't be able to get on
a flight tonight, it's full.

430
00:26:07,053 --> 00:26:09,754
The ticketing agent says the
earliest flight back is tomorrow.

431
00:26:09,844 --> 00:26:12,344
It's done, let's pack up
and go to the airport.

432
00:26:21,595 --> 00:26:22,421
Miss Lui.

433
00:26:22,511 --> 00:26:23,753
This rose is from

434
00:26:23,843 --> 00:26:27,004
Mr Tang's winery in Champagne,
Chateau du Tang.

435
00:26:27,094 --> 00:26:29,129
This rose is called "All My Loving",

436
00:26:29,219 --> 00:26:31,129
It's grown exclusively
at Mr Tang's rose garden.

437
00:26:31,219 --> 00:26:34,129
This is a 77 percent cocoa
dark chocolate,

438
00:26:34,219 --> 00:26:37,088
the latest from
NT and The Chocolate Factory.

439
00:26:37,178 --> 00:26:39,553
- You can leave while you're done.
- Yes, sir.

440
00:26:40,219 --> 00:26:42,969
Eva, guess what
this chocolate is called.

441
00:26:44,344 --> 00:26:46,261
It looks like...

442
00:26:47,094 --> 00:26:50,753
"A melty tear",
like a melting teardrop.

443
00:26:50,843 --> 00:26:52,219
I'm romantic, aren't I?

444
00:26:53,595 --> 00:26:55,088
I'm sorry, Mr Tang,

445
00:26:55,178 --> 00:26:56,713
for having to fly me
back to Hong Kong.

446
00:26:56,803 --> 00:26:57,672
I'll pay you back for the flight.

447
00:26:57,762 --> 00:26:59,879
If I make you pay me back,
then I'd be really sorry.

448
00:26:59,969 --> 00:27:01,796
You're so much poorer than me.

449
00:27:01,886 --> 00:27:03,213
Money is of no object to me,

450
00:27:03,303 --> 00:27:05,796
I value my time
and effort far above that.

451
00:27:05,886 --> 00:27:09,254
Just take some time
to focus on the now,

452
00:27:09,344 --> 00:27:13,046
and get ready to enjoy
the entertainment I've prepared.

453
00:27:13,136 --> 00:27:14,088
Are we watching a movie?

454
00:27:14,178 --> 00:27:15,296
I like watching movies.

455
00:27:15,386 --> 00:27:16,754
I don't talk when I watch movies.

456
00:27:16,844 --> 00:27:18,386
Brilliant minds think alike.

457
00:27:18,927 --> 00:27:20,879
The best entertainment
is chatting with me.

458
00:27:20,969 --> 00:27:21,796
So let's chat,

459
00:27:21,886 --> 00:27:22,880
and you may start now.

460
00:27:23,886 --> 00:27:27,762
- Then, why don't we tell jokes?
- Good idea.

461
00:27:28,011 --> 00:27:29,837
Once, I bought some expensive
caterpillar fungus

462
00:27:29,927 --> 00:27:32,754
and I asked my domestic worker
to cook it.

463
00:27:32,844 --> 00:27:34,921
She brought it over to me,

464
00:27:35,011 --> 00:27:37,129
but I'd actually bought it
for the dog.

465
00:27:37,219 --> 00:27:40,136
I can't believe that
she had no idea, isn't that funny?

466
00:27:42,178 --> 00:27:43,303
Your turn.

467
00:27:46,511 --> 00:27:49,129
I don't have many...

468
00:27:49,219 --> 00:27:51,171
That's hilarious!

469
00:27:51,261 --> 00:27:52,470
That's a good one.

470
00:27:56,636 --> 00:27:58,553
It's fun to tell jokes.

471
00:27:58,844 --> 00:28:04,219
But I'd like to talk to you
about some romantic things,

472
00:28:04,927 --> 00:28:08,636
do you know what GDP stands for?

473
00:28:09,553 --> 00:28:12,303
- Gross Domestic Product?
- Good answer.

474
00:28:13,094 --> 00:28:14,713
Let me tell you a story.

475
00:28:14,803 --> 00:28:16,338
Once there were two economists

476
00:28:16,428 --> 00:28:17,753
named Adam and Smith,

477
00:28:17,843 --> 00:28:21,129
they were taking a stroll together
when they spotted a drop of dog poo.

478
00:28:21,219 --> 00:28:22,879
Adam says to Smith,

479
00:28:22,969 --> 00:28:25,046
"If you eat it,
I'll give you a million dollars."

480
00:28:25,136 --> 00:28:28,254
Smith really eats it,
so Adam gave him a million bucks.

481
00:28:28,344 --> 00:28:31,879
Then, they kept on strolling until
they spotted a drop of cat poo.

482
00:28:31,969 --> 00:28:33,879
This time, Smith says to Adam,

483
00:28:33,969 --> 00:28:35,046
"If you eat it,"

484
00:28:35,136 --> 00:28:36,963
"I'll give you back
your million dollars."

485
00:28:37,053 --> 00:28:38,254
So Adam eats it,

486
00:28:38,344 --> 00:28:41,796
and Smith really does return
the million bucks.

487
00:28:41,886 --> 00:28:43,004
Well, that's dumb.

488
00:28:43,094 --> 00:28:45,921
No one made any money,
but they both ate poo.

489
00:28:46,011 --> 00:28:49,546
But that's not how economists think.

490
00:28:49,636 --> 00:28:52,129
It's true that no one ate money
and both of them ate poo,

491
00:28:52,219 --> 00:28:55,004
but the GDP went up by 2 million.

492
00:28:55,094 --> 00:28:57,171
Everyone feels richer for it.

493
00:28:57,261 --> 00:28:58,927
I'm such a romantic, aren't I?

494
00:29:01,094 --> 00:29:03,927
I'm sleepy,
I'm going to get some sleep.

495
00:29:09,386 --> 00:29:11,428
You really look like my dead mother.

496
00:29:13,178 --> 00:29:15,843
Not when your eyes are opened,
but when they're closed.

497
00:29:18,803 --> 00:29:20,762
She looked just like that
when she died.

498
00:29:23,386 --> 00:29:25,136
She didn't toss around,

499
00:29:26,927 --> 00:29:28,470
and breathed less.

500
00:29:29,844 --> 00:29:31,470
Then, her heart stopped, too.

501
00:29:35,011 --> 00:29:36,963
Your husband died
such an unjust death!

502
00:29:37,053 --> 00:29:38,171
How can you die so early?

503
00:29:38,261 --> 00:29:40,338
Our flat isn't
even paid off yet, son!

504
00:29:40,428 --> 00:29:41,969
Sit down...

505
00:29:43,261 --> 00:29:46,754
- He, he's dead now!
- What will we do about the flat?

506
00:29:46,844 --> 00:29:48,470
- Eva.
- Where's Mom?

507
00:29:49,261 --> 00:29:50,255
Come with me.

508
00:29:50,720 --> 00:29:52,713
- Mom.
- You're back already?

509
00:29:52,803 --> 00:29:54,421
- Are you okay?
- I'm fine.

510
00:29:54,511 --> 00:29:55,463
What did the doctor say?

511
00:29:55,553 --> 00:29:56,796
He says it's a spell of anaemia,

512
00:29:56,886 --> 00:29:58,921
but I think it's better
to get more tests.

513
00:29:59,011 --> 00:30:01,630
- Thank you, Adam.
- You're welcome.

514
00:30:01,720 --> 00:30:03,754
Thank my family's domestic worker
for this.

515
00:30:03,844 --> 00:30:06,129
When my mother was in the hospital,

516
00:30:06,219 --> 00:30:08,129
she made soup for her, too.

517
00:30:08,219 --> 00:30:09,213
Thanks.

518
00:30:13,720 --> 00:30:15,511
- I'll get you some water.
- Let me.

519
00:30:16,053 --> 00:30:17,421
The doctor is coming
on his rounds anytime now,

520
00:30:17,511 --> 00:30:19,595
so you can talk to him directly.

521
00:30:24,053 --> 00:30:25,886
Hey, sit down.

522
00:30:28,762 --> 00:30:31,969
Adam always hangs
around downstairs waiting for you,

523
00:30:32,843 --> 00:30:34,219
but he didn't want you to know.

524
00:30:35,636 --> 00:30:37,428
He brought you to the hospital?

525
00:30:39,261 --> 00:30:41,553
- I'm fine.
- You should lie down.

526
00:30:46,219 --> 00:30:47,213
Would you like dessert?

527
00:30:47,303 --> 00:30:48,753
We have two choices,

528
00:30:48,843 --> 00:30:50,927
blackcurrants cake and macaron.

529
00:30:51,595 --> 00:30:53,421
Definitely not
the blackcurrents cake,

530
00:30:53,511 --> 00:30:55,553
you don't eat processed fruits.

531
00:30:56,386 --> 00:30:57,837
Two macarons, please.

532
00:30:57,927 --> 00:30:59,762
- Sure, two macarons.
- Thanks...

533
00:31:03,386 --> 00:31:05,053
How did you lose your phone?

534
00:31:06,219 --> 00:31:08,296
It's unbelievable,

535
00:31:08,386 --> 00:31:10,470
good thing you knew to call Cat.

536
00:31:11,303 --> 00:31:13,386
Two macarons, thank you.

537
00:31:14,011 --> 00:31:15,261
- Thanks...
- Enjoy.

538
00:31:18,511 --> 00:31:19,505
Have mine too,

539
00:31:19,843 --> 00:31:20,837
I know you like it.

540
00:31:25,219 --> 00:31:26,969
So, how have you been?

541
00:31:28,762 --> 00:31:31,162
My father and stepmom moved back
to Vancouver for retirement,

542
00:31:31,803 --> 00:31:34,261
and he sold his shares
in the law firm to his partners.

543
00:31:37,803 --> 00:31:39,296
You know me,

544
00:31:39,386 --> 00:31:41,879
I never liked working
in my dad's firm.

545
00:31:41,969 --> 00:31:44,762
Besides, mergers and acquisitions
work isn't for me too.

546
00:31:46,011 --> 00:31:48,511
That's good, you can keep
teaching kickboxing then.

547
00:31:49,136 --> 00:31:50,219
I already am.

548
00:31:52,969 --> 00:31:54,178
As long as you're happy.

549
00:31:56,386 --> 00:31:58,129
But I'm also trying new things.

550
00:31:58,219 --> 00:31:59,428
Like what?

551
00:32:01,094 --> 00:32:02,338
Sorry...

552
00:32:02,428 --> 00:32:04,879
I'm interrogating you like a mom.

553
00:32:04,969 --> 00:32:06,546
Never mind, go ahead.

554
00:32:06,636 --> 00:32:09,076
It's been forever since someone
asked me questions like these.

555
00:32:09,886 --> 00:32:11,338
Sorry, it's time for last order,

556
00:32:11,428 --> 00:32:12,678
would you like anything else?

557
00:32:13,094 --> 00:32:14,088
I'm full.

558
00:32:14,553 --> 00:32:16,219
- The check, please.
- Sure, thank you.

559
00:32:19,678 --> 00:32:20,672
Thanks.

560
00:32:21,844 --> 00:32:22,753
Are you okay?

561
00:32:22,843 --> 00:32:25,595
Just some gas,
I'll be fine after I take my pills.

562
00:32:32,303 --> 00:32:34,254
Say, did you receive
my text message?

563
00:32:34,344 --> 00:32:35,762
What message?

564
00:32:40,511 --> 00:32:41,505
Never mind.

565
00:32:46,927 --> 00:32:48,004
Is there any doubt?

566
00:32:48,094 --> 00:32:51,344
I'm 100 percent sure that he wants
to win you back with that message.

567
00:32:51,886 --> 00:32:55,254
He's been on probation for a year,
it's time to absolve him now.

568
00:32:55,344 --> 00:32:59,088
Feelings change, but people don't.

569
00:32:59,178 --> 00:33:01,219
What will you do, Eva?

570
00:33:01,927 --> 00:33:04,171
Nothing,
I'll just take the world as it is.

571
00:33:04,261 --> 00:33:07,753
- I want to see a happy ending!
- No way.

572
00:33:07,843 --> 00:33:10,261
Adam should've known better,
am I right?

573
00:33:10,511 --> 00:33:12,171
It's good to stay single,

574
00:33:12,261 --> 00:33:14,546
live worry-free
and you can go anywhere you want.

575
00:33:14,636 --> 00:33:16,129
You're just boring,

576
00:33:16,219 --> 00:33:17,539
I'm going to ignore your opinion.

577
00:33:17,636 --> 00:33:20,088
I have the longest CV
when it comes to relationships,

578
00:33:20,178 --> 00:33:21,004
just trust me on this.

579
00:33:21,094 --> 00:33:23,470
Oh, shut up already.
You think you're a judge?

580
00:33:23,636 --> 00:33:26,254
Court...

581
00:33:26,344 --> 00:33:28,595
- The trial is in session.
- A trial?

582
00:33:29,219 --> 00:33:30,672
Are you kidding me?

583
00:33:30,762 --> 00:33:31,636
Silence!

584
00:33:31,762 --> 00:33:32,753
Your Honor,

585
00:33:32,843 --> 00:33:35,511
I object to our Plaintiff
getting back with the Defendant.

586
00:33:37,428 --> 00:33:38,672
In the words of Albert Einstein,

587
00:33:38,762 --> 00:33:41,046
"A woman who repeats
the same mistake"

588
00:33:41,136 --> 00:33:42,338
"will suffer the same fate,"

589
00:33:42,428 --> 00:33:44,713
"no matter
how many times she tries."

590
00:33:44,803 --> 00:33:46,386
When did Einstein say that?

591
00:33:46,844 --> 00:33:48,380
Your Honor, I hold evidence

592
00:33:48,470 --> 00:33:50,879
proving that the Plaintiff still
misses the Defendant.

593
00:33:50,969 --> 00:33:52,843
Even your phone still misses Adam?

594
00:33:54,344 --> 00:33:56,004
I wanna help my Best-friend-forever
to pick a wedding dress.

595
00:33:56,094 --> 00:33:58,546
Objection, I don't want to wear
another bridesmaid dress!

596
00:33:58,636 --> 00:34:00,380
Besides, I don't get
why people still get married.

597
00:34:00,470 --> 00:34:01,338
Your Honor,

598
00:34:01,428 --> 00:34:05,595
evidence shows that there are plenty
of great guys waiting for her.

599
00:34:07,136 --> 00:34:09,505
For example,
my crazy rich boss, NT Tang.

600
00:34:09,595 --> 00:34:12,046
Everyone, for the Plaintiff.

601
00:34:12,136 --> 00:34:13,004
Money is not
the most important thing.

602
00:34:13,094 --> 00:34:16,129
The most important thing is
that modern women have a choice,

603
00:34:16,219 --> 00:34:17,754
it's no crime to be single!

604
00:34:17,844 --> 00:34:19,004
Yet, a lot of women
search day and night,

605
00:34:19,094 --> 00:34:20,088
only to still end up with scraps.

606
00:34:20,178 --> 00:34:21,963
Let's hear some objective facts
from the Plaintiff.

607
00:34:22,053 --> 00:34:24,546
We have to consider the
Plaintiff's best interest.

608
00:34:24,636 --> 00:34:26,963
I see her in the office every day,

609
00:34:27,053 --> 00:34:28,004
I'm the only one
who truly understands her.

610
00:34:28,094 --> 00:34:29,380
- No, I understand her the most.
- I understand her so much more.

611
00:34:29,470 --> 00:34:30,553
Silence!

612
00:34:31,511 --> 00:34:34,428
Or I'll disbar all of you.

613
00:34:35,136 --> 00:34:37,636
Eva Lui, what do you
have to say for yourself?

614
00:34:40,803 --> 00:34:45,011
I want to tell the world
at this moment that you, Eva Lui,

615
00:34:46,261 --> 00:34:48,178
taught me all about...

616
00:34:54,595 --> 00:34:55,843
Love!

617
00:34:56,428 --> 00:34:59,636
I, Eva Lui, want to tell the world

618
00:34:59,969 --> 00:35:02,762
that the only person I love
is my mother.

619
00:35:13,178 --> 00:35:14,172
Lin?

620
00:35:14,470 --> 00:35:15,464
Is that Lin?

621
00:35:17,011 --> 00:35:18,303
Po-wah!

622
00:35:18,511 --> 00:35:19,505
Are you Po-wah?

623
00:35:20,595 --> 00:35:22,428
I've been looking for you
for 40 years!

624
00:35:23,886 --> 00:35:25,219
You haven't changed one bit.

625
00:35:25,595 --> 00:35:29,004
- Your eyes are just getting old.
- No way.

626
00:35:29,094 --> 00:35:31,494
I just had the cataract surgery
last year, and I am good now.

627
00:35:33,303 --> 00:35:35,595
We've both grown so old.

628
00:35:37,843 --> 00:35:38,921
I'm so happy.

629
00:35:39,011 --> 00:35:40,921
If we hadn't come in
for maintenance at the same time,

630
00:35:41,011 --> 00:35:42,511
we wouldn't have met again.

631
00:35:43,219 --> 00:35:45,261
Just a coincidence, that's all.

632
00:35:46,803 --> 00:35:51,553
To be honest, after losing touch
all those years ago,

633
00:35:52,428 --> 00:35:55,844
I never found another girlfriend
as compatible as you.

634
00:35:58,094 --> 00:36:00,762
- How have you been?
- I've been well.

635
00:36:01,136 --> 00:36:03,713
I have a daughter,
she's all grown up now.

636
00:36:03,803 --> 00:36:04,796
She's a lawyer.

637
00:36:04,886 --> 00:36:05,880
Here.

638
00:36:06,386 --> 00:36:07,470
I'll show you.

639
00:36:08,803 --> 00:36:09,797
She's awfully pretty.

640
00:36:09,969 --> 00:36:10,963
Like you.

641
00:36:12,553 --> 00:36:16,219
This guy is the boyfriend
she's always arguing with.

642
00:36:22,969 --> 00:36:23,963
Why did you pick him?

643
00:36:24,053 --> 00:36:25,636
My mother made the call.

644
00:36:26,470 --> 00:36:28,178
I went on a lot of arranged dates.

645
00:36:29,178 --> 00:36:30,511
Out of all the guys I met,

646
00:36:31,595 --> 00:36:34,136
he's the one
that looked the most like you.

647
00:36:41,011 --> 00:36:43,843
Did he treat you as well as I did?

648
00:36:44,553 --> 00:36:46,754
For better or worse,
we had a life together.

649
00:36:46,844 --> 00:36:48,511
It went by in the blink of an eye.

650
00:36:50,762 --> 00:36:51,969
He's passed away now.

651
00:36:52,511 --> 00:36:54,762
I don't know
how long I'll last, either.

652
00:36:55,636 --> 00:36:56,505
Don't say that.

653
00:36:56,595 --> 00:36:59,754
Hong Kong women have the longest
life expectancy in the world,

654
00:36:59,844 --> 00:37:01,303
which even longer than the men.

655
00:37:03,303 --> 00:37:04,844
What are you in the hospital for?

656
00:37:05,969 --> 00:37:06,879
I'll give you three choices.

657
00:37:06,969 --> 00:37:08,213
I'll buy you an ice cream
cone if you get it right.

658
00:37:08,303 --> 00:37:09,171
A, the three highs.

659
00:37:09,261 --> 00:37:10,129
B, a stroke.

660
00:37:10,219 --> 00:37:11,129
C, cancer.

661
00:37:11,219 --> 00:37:12,254
Don't joke about that,

662
00:37:12,344 --> 00:37:14,296
I can't handle the shock.

663
00:37:14,386 --> 00:37:16,879
I'm easygoing
about my own mortality now,

664
00:37:16,969 --> 00:37:18,713
I just miss my friends.

665
00:37:18,803 --> 00:37:21,219
I worked as a tour guide
for 40 years.

666
00:37:21,803 --> 00:37:23,088
I've been all over the world

667
00:37:23,178 --> 00:37:25,963
and I've seen all kinds of things.

668
00:37:26,053 --> 00:37:27,213
You're lucky,

669
00:37:27,303 --> 00:37:29,463
I just convince myself
I've been to a place

670
00:37:29,553 --> 00:37:31,553
after seeing it on a travel show.

671
00:37:32,511 --> 00:37:33,927
You've led a fortunate life.

672
00:37:36,595 --> 00:37:38,969
The only regret is
I couldn't marry my first love.

673
00:37:39,886 --> 00:37:42,261
Look at how old we are,
no point talking about that.

674
00:37:46,053 --> 00:37:47,386
How did you end up in here, then?

675
00:37:48,553 --> 00:37:52,553
I fainted on the street,
the doctor says it's anaemia.

676
00:37:53,011 --> 00:37:56,428
The tests are taking forever.

677
00:37:57,927 --> 00:37:59,546
Do you have diabetes?

678
00:37:59,636 --> 00:38:02,380
If you don't,
let's go get an ice cream gone.

679
00:38:02,470 --> 00:38:03,796
The convenient store
in this hospital

680
00:38:03,886 --> 00:38:05,927
has that Apollo brand
that we used to love,

681
00:38:06,178 --> 00:38:07,053
how's that sound?

682
00:38:07,261 --> 00:38:09,129
You're so nostalgic.

683
00:38:09,219 --> 00:38:11,762
The old is new again, come on.

684
00:38:12,595 --> 00:38:13,505
Where do you live now?

685
00:38:13,595 --> 00:38:16,969
- Not far from here.
- Is that so?

686
00:38:20,762 --> 00:38:22,762
- Hey, Adam.
- Sorry.

687
00:38:23,219 --> 00:38:24,213
What's up?

688
00:38:24,886 --> 00:38:27,303
Your ex-student is over there.

689
00:38:27,428 --> 00:38:29,129
When I paid the tuition fee,

690
00:38:29,219 --> 00:38:30,754
you guys said
that it can be refunded.

691
00:38:30,844 --> 00:38:31,879
- No...
- So what should I do?

692
00:38:31,969 --> 00:38:33,546
Should I report you
to the Consumer Council?

693
00:38:33,636 --> 00:38:35,046
Company policies state that

694
00:38:35,136 --> 00:38:37,296
a refund is only possible
under special circumstances.

695
00:38:37,386 --> 00:38:38,879
According to our records,

696
00:38:38,969 --> 00:38:40,921
you've never called
to make a leave of absence.

697
00:38:41,011 --> 00:38:43,636
It's your trainer
that doesn't want to train me,

698
00:38:43,762 --> 00:38:46,344
I didn't even have a chance
to take a leave of absence.

699
00:38:46,511 --> 00:38:48,303
- Let me handle this.
- Sure.

700
00:38:54,762 --> 00:38:56,428
Sorry,
there was a long line at the ATM.

701
00:38:57,511 --> 00:38:58,886
Your refund, please count it.

702
00:39:02,303 --> 00:39:03,553
I threw away the old one.

703
00:39:06,969 --> 00:39:08,011
Clearing your debt?

704
00:39:10,011 --> 00:39:11,004
How's your Eva?

705
00:39:11,094 --> 00:39:12,636
We almost got back together,

706
00:39:12,762 --> 00:39:14,088
but your contact lens
case ruined it.

707
00:39:14,178 --> 00:39:16,088
I returned her notebook to you.

708
00:39:16,178 --> 00:39:17,386
And that contact lens case?

709
00:39:18,344 --> 00:39:20,053
Did you leave it behind on purpose?

710
00:39:21,762 --> 00:39:22,756
I don't know.

711
00:39:23,261 --> 00:39:24,963
Even if I did,

712
00:39:25,053 --> 00:39:27,344
you should've known it wasn't Eva's.

713
00:39:27,886 --> 00:39:29,421
Blame yourself for being dumb.

714
00:39:29,511 --> 00:39:30,546
Without a backup phone like me,

715
00:39:30,636 --> 00:39:32,837
how would you know how much
you missed your primary phone?

716
00:39:32,927 --> 00:39:34,636
All your memories, social media,

717
00:39:34,762 --> 00:39:36,129
everything important in your life

718
00:39:36,219 --> 00:39:38,046
was in that primary phone,
after all.

719
00:39:38,136 --> 00:39:40,921
You were even crying "Eva..."
when you were drunk.

720
00:39:41,011 --> 00:39:44,136
Anyway, be careful
meeting people next time.

721
00:39:47,762 --> 00:39:52,219
I really hate you,
but I really like you, too.

722
00:39:53,470 --> 00:39:54,803
Still got my phone number?

723
00:39:55,344 --> 00:39:56,254
I've deleted it already.

724
00:39:56,344 --> 00:39:57,338
I'm heading back now.

725
00:39:57,927 --> 00:39:59,927
It's okay, I still have your number.

726
00:40:09,053 --> 00:40:13,094
"5th, 77 Heartwarmings"

727
00:40:14,178 --> 00:40:15,754
I have good news.

728
00:40:15,844 --> 00:40:20,011
I'm going to marry Mandy,
whom I've only known for 3 days.

729
00:40:21,511 --> 00:40:23,053
Sorry, I'm still in love with her.

730
00:40:32,803 --> 00:40:35,344
"Message from Anon"

731
00:40:38,094 --> 00:40:39,511
"Anon"

732
00:40:46,969 --> 00:40:49,261
"Loading"

733
00:40:49,927 --> 00:40:52,094
"77 Heartwarmings"

734
00:41:00,470 --> 00:41:02,129
Marvel, get some rest.

735
00:41:02,219 --> 00:41:05,713
We'll head to the airport
in three hours, okay?

736
00:41:05,803 --> 00:41:07,303
Sure, see you soon.

737
00:41:23,595 --> 00:41:25,171
Dear Melody,

738
00:41:25,261 --> 00:41:27,004
if you want a happy ending,

739
00:41:27,094 --> 00:41:29,844
it depends where you want to
stop the story.

740
00:41:30,470 --> 00:41:34,254
You can always start a new scene
and give it some happiness.

741
00:41:34,344 --> 00:41:37,470
If you believe in it,
your dreams will come true.

742
00:41:38,136 --> 00:41:39,796
Melody is your name,

743
00:41:39,886 --> 00:41:41,927
let's play a joyful tune
in your heart.

744
00:41:42,219 --> 00:41:43,213
From Marvel.

745
00:41:47,094 --> 00:41:48,713
"Tom Yum Goong"

746
00:41:48,803 --> 00:41:50,428
"I'll be in Hong Kong tomorrow"

747
00:42:00,969 --> 00:42:04,011
"Let her know
what you're doing right now"

748
00:42:14,136 --> 00:42:17,720
"I'm waiting for a job interview,
I'm a little nervous"

749
00:42:36,886 --> 00:42:39,129
"I want to go to your place
to pick up some things,"

750
00:42:39,219 --> 00:42:41,219
"is it okay?"

751
00:42:43,553 --> 00:42:46,261
"You can come home anytime."

752
00:42:57,762 --> 00:42:58,713
"NT Tang"

753
00:42:58,803 --> 00:42:59,921
"I want to tell you"

754
00:43:00,011 --> 00:43:01,261
"that what I'm doing right now"

755
00:43:09,428 --> 00:43:13,754
Eva, what I'm doing now is called
Shitali Pranayama yoga,

756
00:43:13,844 --> 00:43:15,837
it means cooling breath.

757
00:43:15,927 --> 00:43:17,753
The key is in the breathing,

758
00:43:17,843 --> 00:43:19,296
so the nostrils are
really important.

759
00:43:19,386 --> 00:43:20,843
Come on, closer.

760
00:43:21,219 --> 00:43:23,088
You must find this interesting, Eva.

761
00:43:23,178 --> 00:43:24,921
I'll show you how to do it.

762
00:43:25,011 --> 00:43:26,713
Press on the right nostril

763
00:43:26,803 --> 00:43:28,505
with your left index finger
and breathe.

764
00:43:28,595 --> 00:43:32,636
One, two, three.

765
00:43:32,762 --> 00:43:36,879
Then press on the left nostril
with your right index finger.

766
00:43:36,969 --> 00:43:39,969
Let go of your left hand,
then breathe.

767
00:43:40,595 --> 00:43:43,129
One, two, three.

768
00:43:43,219 --> 00:43:44,505
The last step is a little hard,

769
00:43:44,595 --> 00:43:46,837
you have to
take your two index fingers

770
00:43:46,927 --> 00:43:49,463
and press down
on both your nostrils,

771
00:43:49,553 --> 00:43:52,261
then even curl up your tongue.

772
00:43:53,886 --> 00:43:57,219
One, two, three.

773
00:44:10,595 --> 00:44:11,595
Mom.

774
00:44:12,927 --> 00:44:14,053
You're here.

775
00:44:14,762 --> 00:44:15,837
What's with all the ice cream?

776
00:44:15,927 --> 00:44:18,505
Sweets make me happy,

777
00:44:18,595 --> 00:44:21,088
and I had a nice dream last night.

778
00:44:21,178 --> 00:44:22,386
What happened?

779
00:44:22,886 --> 00:44:24,261
I dreamt your wedding.

780
00:44:26,261 --> 00:44:29,296
You know, you had a beautiful
wedding dress on.

781
00:44:29,386 --> 00:44:31,886
Just when I was about
to reach out and touch it,

782
00:44:32,386 --> 00:44:34,843
that nurse woke me up.

783
00:44:37,428 --> 00:44:38,754
No, I can't do this.

784
00:44:38,844 --> 00:44:42,178
Marvel, please don't be upset.

785
00:44:42,470 --> 00:44:44,546
You read the script?
It's ridiculous.

786
00:44:44,636 --> 00:44:46,505
The father dies, the mother dies,

787
00:44:46,595 --> 00:44:48,713
the son dies, the daughter dies...

788
00:44:48,803 --> 00:44:50,754
I die, everybody dies.

789
00:44:50,844 --> 00:44:53,129
Exactly, we all die in the end.

790
00:44:53,219 --> 00:44:56,219
Ginny, you better
talk to the studio again.

791
00:44:57,261 --> 00:45:00,254
This is no use,
the studio won't change the script

792
00:45:00,344 --> 00:45:02,213
nor will they change
the contract we signed.

793
00:45:02,303 --> 00:45:04,421
It doesn't matter
where we are heading to,

794
00:45:04,511 --> 00:45:06,380
there is only one map
to the journey of life

795
00:45:06,470 --> 00:45:08,136
and it lives within our hearts.

796
00:45:26,011 --> 00:45:27,053
"Stage 2"

797
00:45:27,511 --> 00:45:29,963
"Move of the day"

798
00:45:30,053 --> 00:45:32,386
"Have dinner with her"

799
00:45:56,011 --> 00:45:57,005
Welcome home.

800
00:46:04,636 --> 00:46:06,261
You're into gaming now?

801
00:46:06,762 --> 00:46:08,171
And you're reading
psychology books too?

802
00:46:08,261 --> 00:46:09,636
Don't have much else to do.

803
00:46:10,344 --> 00:46:13,053
It's not like you to be this neat.

804
00:46:15,219 --> 00:46:16,837
Why do you sit on the floor
instead of the sofa?

805
00:46:16,927 --> 00:46:18,011
It's easier for work.

806
00:46:18,636 --> 00:46:19,630
Like this.

807
00:46:21,178 --> 00:46:23,171
- What's going on? Where?
- A cockroach!

808
00:46:23,261 --> 00:46:24,303
Under the monitor.

809
00:46:24,511 --> 00:46:25,713
The neighbor didn't put the lid on
the trash bin again!

810
00:46:25,803 --> 00:46:26,921
Stay off my keyboard!

811
00:46:27,011 --> 00:46:28,088
Off the keyboard!

812
00:46:28,178 --> 00:46:30,754
- Go away...
- Not my book!

813
00:46:30,844 --> 00:46:33,886
- Don't be scared.
- Help me!

814
00:46:39,843 --> 00:46:40,753
Good thing you were here.

815
00:46:40,843 --> 00:46:42,672
I was scared, too, but look at you.

816
00:46:42,762 --> 00:46:45,053
You were freaked out,
so what else was I supposed to do?

817
00:46:45,844 --> 00:46:47,094
Do you think it's really dead?

818
00:46:48,094 --> 00:46:49,094
Wait, what are you doing?

819
00:46:49,344 --> 00:46:51,004
It's a bookmark now!

820
00:46:51,094 --> 00:46:52,796
Can I borrow your bathroom?

821
00:46:52,886 --> 00:46:54,386
It's your home, too.

822
00:46:55,261 --> 00:46:56,720
I'll give it an ocean burial.

823
00:46:58,678 --> 00:46:59,844
Then I'll go steam the fish.

824
00:47:18,094 --> 00:47:20,470
Did you see
how well he cleaned the place?

825
00:47:20,844 --> 00:47:22,546
Of course he did,
because you're not around.

826
00:47:22,636 --> 00:47:26,546
It means everything you did
were in vain.

827
00:47:26,636 --> 00:47:29,338
There was a lot happening
in his family back then.

828
00:47:29,428 --> 00:47:31,879
There was his dad's divorce,
then his mom got sick.

829
00:47:31,969 --> 00:47:34,338
He was so upset,
how could I bother him?

830
00:47:34,428 --> 00:47:37,713
And now, he's got nothing better
to do than to play games.

831
00:47:37,803 --> 00:47:39,553
That's called passion.

832
00:47:39,844 --> 00:47:42,213
People need to have hobbies,
you know.

833
00:47:42,303 --> 00:47:44,754
That's not what you used to say.

834
00:47:44,844 --> 00:47:46,171
Don't say I didn't warn you.

835
00:47:46,261 --> 00:47:47,380
When a man wants you back,

836
00:47:47,470 --> 00:47:49,546
it's natural that
he'll show you his best side.

837
00:47:49,636 --> 00:47:52,171
Once you're hooked,
he returns to his old ways.

838
00:47:52,261 --> 00:47:55,046
I don't get why
you're always so negative.

839
00:47:55,136 --> 00:47:58,380
You didn't come back for your stuff,

840
00:47:58,470 --> 00:48:03,046
but wanted to see if other girls
left anything in the bathroom again.

841
00:48:03,136 --> 00:48:04,463
I don't have time to argue with you,

842
00:48:04,553 --> 00:48:06,927
a steamed fish is best served hot.

843
00:48:47,969 --> 00:48:50,178
Hey, what were you doing
on that bridge?

844
00:48:51,595 --> 00:48:52,636
What?

845
00:48:53,136 --> 00:48:54,261
Dinner's ready.

846
00:48:56,094 --> 00:48:57,219
Let's give this a try.

847
00:49:08,511 --> 00:49:11,303
Say, how did your interview go?

848
00:49:13,219 --> 00:49:15,219
They said
that I gave the best answer.

849
00:49:16,094 --> 00:49:17,886
What was the question?

850
00:49:19,219 --> 00:49:20,753
Imagine.

851
00:49:20,843 --> 00:49:24,879
There's a blizzard outside
while you're driving home,

852
00:49:24,969 --> 00:49:26,296
and there are only
two seats in the car.

853
00:49:26,386 --> 00:49:28,004
The blizzard's getting worse,

854
00:49:28,094 --> 00:49:29,837
then you drive past a bus stop.

855
00:49:29,927 --> 00:49:32,296
You know that the bus only comes
once every three hours,

856
00:49:32,386 --> 00:49:34,421
and there are three people waiting.

857
00:49:34,511 --> 00:49:37,213
The first person
is your best friend.

858
00:49:37,303 --> 00:49:40,129
The second person
is a sick old lady.

859
00:49:40,219 --> 00:49:42,754
And the third person
is your dream girl.

860
00:49:42,844 --> 00:49:45,213
Remember,
your car only has two seats.

861
00:49:45,303 --> 00:49:47,063
If you were the driver,
how would you choose?

862
00:49:47,470 --> 00:49:50,678
Knowing you,
you'd drive your friend.

863
00:49:51,843 --> 00:49:52,837
Nope.

864
00:49:53,094 --> 00:49:54,004
Maybe the old lady?

865
00:49:54,094 --> 00:49:55,843
You did drive my mother
to the hospital.

866
00:49:57,470 --> 00:49:59,588
Not the dream girl, right?

867
00:49:59,678 --> 00:50:01,358
You'd fail the interview
by answering that.

868
00:50:03,261 --> 00:50:04,261
Then what did you say?

869
00:50:05,178 --> 00:50:06,004
I...

870
00:50:06,094 --> 00:50:07,344
Excuse me.

871
00:50:11,843 --> 00:50:13,762
- Hello?
- Hey, want your phone back?

872
00:50:14,136 --> 00:50:16,338
Of course, it's very important.

873
00:50:16,428 --> 00:50:18,969
- Do you know any good lawyer?
- Yes.

874
00:50:19,678 --> 00:50:20,636
I need your help,

875
00:50:20,762 --> 00:50:22,803
please come to
Wan Chai police station.

876
00:50:25,969 --> 00:50:27,470
Okay, I'm coming.

877
00:50:27,636 --> 00:50:30,136
Sorry, I have to go.

878
00:50:30,720 --> 00:50:32,303
- Is everything okay?
- I am sorry.

879
00:50:34,344 --> 00:50:35,886
What's wrong? Do you need a ride?

880
00:50:36,969 --> 00:50:38,969
No, I'll just get a taxi.

881
00:50:40,636 --> 00:50:41,843
Thanks for the dinner.

882
00:50:42,803 --> 00:50:43,797
Bye.

883
00:50:45,094 --> 00:50:46,219
Be careful.

884
00:50:50,762 --> 00:50:52,720
- You can go now.
- Okay.

885
00:50:53,803 --> 00:50:55,844
- These are your belongings.
- Yes.

886
00:50:57,344 --> 00:50:58,338
Sign here.

887
00:51:13,843 --> 00:51:15,886
- Where's my...
- Thank you for bailing me out.

888
00:51:18,094 --> 00:51:19,129
Where's my phone?

889
00:51:19,219 --> 00:51:20,927
Oh, yes, sure.

890
00:51:24,803 --> 00:51:25,879
I need to work tomorrow.

891
00:51:25,969 --> 00:51:28,720
If I couldn't get out,
I'd be in big trouble.

892
00:51:32,344 --> 00:51:34,754
You're already in a big trouble
in the first place,

893
00:51:34,844 --> 00:51:36,762
that's why you couldn't get out.

894
00:51:38,886 --> 00:51:39,927
Where's the lawyer?

895
00:51:41,011 --> 00:51:42,005
Me.

896
00:51:43,053 --> 00:51:45,844
Eva, please charge me.

897
00:51:46,219 --> 00:51:47,636
May I have your business card?

898
00:51:48,386 --> 00:51:49,380
Sure.

899
00:51:50,219 --> 00:51:52,254
So should I bill Space-time Intruder

900
00:51:52,344 --> 00:51:53,844
or Marvel?

901
00:51:54,843 --> 00:51:56,088
You watch my movies?

902
00:51:56,178 --> 00:51:59,636
Come on, your phone advertisements
are everywhere.

903
00:52:01,011 --> 00:52:02,178
Will you keep my secret?

904
00:52:02,636 --> 00:52:03,630
Which one?

905
00:52:04,094 --> 00:52:07,754
You mean the real identity
of Space-time Intruder?

906
00:52:07,844 --> 00:52:11,046
Or the arrest of
the Thai movie star, Marvel?

907
00:52:11,136 --> 00:52:14,344
Listen, I can't let anyone know
about my secret.

908
00:52:14,553 --> 00:52:16,004
It would be damaging to me,

909
00:52:16,094 --> 00:52:18,879
my clients, my agent and my fans.

910
00:52:18,969 --> 00:52:23,004
So you're asking me
to shut up about your mistakes?

911
00:52:23,094 --> 00:52:24,463
I'm hiring you as my lawyer,

912
00:52:24,553 --> 00:52:26,463
we can sign
a confidentality agreement about it

913
00:52:26,553 --> 00:52:28,046
and you can charge me
double or triple.

914
00:52:28,136 --> 00:52:29,963
Okay, I'll consider it.

915
00:52:30,053 --> 00:52:31,047
Bye.

916
00:52:32,511 --> 00:52:34,136
Hey, one more thing.

917
00:52:36,927 --> 00:52:39,344
I think you should
go back with that Adam guy.

918
00:52:40,094 --> 00:52:43,303
Wait, you checked my messages?

919
00:52:43,927 --> 00:52:45,796
Adam's messages are sincere,

920
00:52:45,886 --> 00:52:47,004
please don't ruin the happy ending.

921
00:52:47,094 --> 00:52:49,129
You have no right
to intrude my privacy,

922
00:52:49,219 --> 00:52:51,754
and please stop telling me
what to do with my life.

923
00:52:51,844 --> 00:52:54,463
You know nothing about me,
nor anything about him.

924
00:52:54,553 --> 00:52:56,088
It's none of your business,

925
00:52:56,178 --> 00:52:58,344
I'm not even a fan of yours!

926
00:53:01,803 --> 00:53:04,636
Cool, no one talks to me
like you do.

927
00:53:08,261 --> 00:53:09,754
Adam, a student's waiting for you.

928
00:53:09,844 --> 00:53:10,753
Again?

929
00:53:10,843 --> 00:53:12,463
I already gave her back her money.

930
00:53:12,553 --> 00:53:15,129
It's a new student,
he was here before we opened.

931
00:53:15,219 --> 00:53:16,428
Thanks.

932
00:53:17,470 --> 00:53:19,386
His name is Marvel,
he doesn't speak Chinese.

933
00:53:22,595 --> 00:53:23,879
- Hi.
- So you're Adam?

934
00:53:23,969 --> 00:53:25,927
Yeah, and you must be Marvel.

935
00:53:26,762 --> 00:53:28,046
How do you know me?

936
00:53:28,136 --> 00:53:30,421
We have a common friend
on social media,

937
00:53:30,511 --> 00:53:31,671
so I want to get to know you.

938
00:53:31,762 --> 00:53:33,129
Nice to meet you.

939
00:53:33,219 --> 00:53:35,380
- Where are you from?
- Thailand.

940
00:53:35,470 --> 00:53:37,595
- Do you know Muay Thai?
- Yeah, a little bit.

941
00:53:38,178 --> 00:53:40,046
But I practice kickboxing more.

942
00:53:40,136 --> 00:53:41,130
Let's try.

943
00:53:41,595 --> 00:53:42,589
Sure.

944
00:53:51,386 --> 00:53:54,046
I know him, he's a movie star!

945
00:53:54,136 --> 00:53:55,927
No wonder he looks so familiar.

946
00:54:02,053 --> 00:54:03,844
He doesn't look like
he's here to learn.

947
00:54:04,219 --> 00:54:05,921
He's here to pick a fight.

948
00:54:06,011 --> 00:54:07,171
Show me your kickboxing.

949
00:54:07,261 --> 00:54:08,386
Show me your Muay Thai.

950
00:54:40,470 --> 00:54:42,219
You're not looking for a teacher,

951
00:54:43,803 --> 00:54:45,386
you're looking for a contender.

952
00:54:46,386 --> 00:54:48,720
It's not easy
to find a contender like you.

953
00:54:49,011 --> 00:54:50,005
Same here.

954
00:54:51,053 --> 00:54:52,553
- See you next time.
- Sure.

955
00:55:09,636 --> 00:55:12,213
You haven't changed one bit,
who is still eating too slow.

956
00:55:12,303 --> 00:55:13,754
You haven't changed, either.

957
00:55:13,844 --> 00:55:17,636
Still eating too fast,
and getting it all over your mouth.

958
00:55:19,844 --> 00:55:22,213
Ice cream melts, doesn't it?

959
00:55:22,303 --> 00:55:23,254
Every ice cream cone

960
00:55:23,344 --> 00:55:25,338
is like a race against time.

961
00:55:25,428 --> 00:55:26,963
And who won?

962
00:55:27,053 --> 00:55:28,047
Well, you see?

963
00:55:28,386 --> 00:55:30,796
In all my years
of traveling around the world

964
00:55:30,886 --> 00:55:31,879
and meeting different people,

965
00:55:31,969 --> 00:55:33,380
no one's ever beaten time.

966
00:55:33,470 --> 00:55:37,344
That's why you should savor it,
make it worth your while.

967
00:55:42,553 --> 00:55:43,547
Lin.

968
00:55:45,053 --> 00:55:48,837
We'd agreed to elope back then,
why didn't you show up?

969
00:55:48,927 --> 00:55:50,178
My family was against it.

970
00:55:51,843 --> 00:55:53,303
We can't be selfish.

971
00:55:57,927 --> 00:56:00,636
Since then, I'd miss you
whenever I eat an ice cream cone

972
00:56:01,762 --> 00:56:02,927
and wherever I go.

973
00:56:05,511 --> 00:56:07,171
There's an ice cream shop in Okinawa

974
00:56:07,261 --> 00:56:08,969
that I'm dying to show you.

975
00:56:09,136 --> 00:56:10,843
- Take me there when I'm better.
- Sure.

976
00:56:14,219 --> 00:56:15,213
Why are you so late?

977
00:56:16,886 --> 00:56:18,421
I was supposed to take my mom home,

978
00:56:18,511 --> 00:56:20,296
but she got a headache.

979
00:56:20,386 --> 00:56:22,754
So I stayed with her
while the doctor checked on her.

980
00:56:22,844 --> 00:56:23,921
It's that bad?

981
00:56:24,011 --> 00:56:27,046
I don't even know
if she really has anaemia,

982
00:56:27,136 --> 00:56:29,088
she told the doctor
totally different things.

983
00:56:29,178 --> 00:56:31,969
Anyway, she needs to do more tests
in the hospital.

984
00:56:32,927 --> 00:56:34,088
Like Spider-Man says,

985
00:56:34,178 --> 00:56:36,553
"With great power
comes great responsibility."

986
00:56:37,261 --> 00:56:38,296
But I'm the opposite one.

987
00:56:38,386 --> 00:56:41,546
With great responsibilities
come great power.

988
00:56:41,636 --> 00:56:44,303
I'm not Spider-Man,
I'm just a normal human being.

989
00:56:46,762 --> 00:56:49,136
There are three surprises
for you today.

990
00:56:50,636 --> 00:56:51,630
Congratulations.

991
00:56:51,844 --> 00:56:52,796
For what?

992
00:56:52,886 --> 00:56:55,178
I've done some checking for you.

993
00:56:55,844 --> 00:56:58,011
"Move of the day, send her flowers"

994
00:56:58,136 --> 00:57:00,254
This is an app called
"77 Heartwarmings",

995
00:57:00,344 --> 00:57:01,338
which is huge right now.

996
00:57:01,886 --> 00:57:02,880
Let's see who sent them.

997
00:57:04,428 --> 00:57:05,927
NT Tang.

998
00:57:07,303 --> 00:57:08,297
Adam.

999
00:57:09,720 --> 00:57:11,927
Anon? Who's that?

1000
00:57:15,219 --> 00:57:17,421
- Hello?
- Eva, call from the police station.

1001
00:57:17,511 --> 00:57:19,254
- Please put it on hold.
- Sure.

1002
00:57:19,344 --> 00:57:21,254
Get me the template
for the confidentiality agreement.

1003
00:57:21,344 --> 00:57:24,386
- Sure, give me the client's name.
- It's confidential.

1004
00:57:25,219 --> 00:57:27,470
You and your secrecy...

1005
00:57:32,803 --> 00:57:33,797
Cut!

1006
00:57:39,219 --> 00:57:41,303
This is
the confidentality agreement.

1007
00:57:41,553 --> 00:57:44,171
Let me explain, first...

1008
00:57:44,261 --> 00:57:45,713
You shouldn't sign anything

1009
00:57:45,803 --> 00:57:48,171
before you understand
the terms and conditions.

1010
00:57:48,261 --> 00:57:49,428
I trust my lawyer.

1011
00:57:50,053 --> 00:57:51,470
I appreciate that,

1012
00:57:51,969 --> 00:57:54,421
but reality is not like movies.

1013
00:57:54,511 --> 00:57:57,219
You're the only person
who knows both sides of me.

1014
00:57:57,969 --> 00:58:01,011
Anyway, they won't press
any charges for now.

1015
00:58:01,678 --> 00:58:02,963
So you're my lucky star.

1016
00:58:03,053 --> 00:58:06,046
But still,
the way you do art is illegal.

1017
00:58:06,136 --> 00:58:08,011
I won't bail you out next time.

1018
00:58:08,136 --> 00:58:09,130
"Understand".

1019
00:58:10,178 --> 00:58:11,553
It means "I understand".

1020
00:58:15,428 --> 00:58:16,511
Let me walk you out.

1021
00:58:18,595 --> 00:58:19,463
When I'm on set,

1022
00:58:19,553 --> 00:58:21,844
it feels like
I'm traveling through a time tunnel.

1023
00:58:22,053 --> 00:58:23,505
People only live once,

1024
00:58:23,595 --> 00:58:26,136
but you can live as many lives
as you want.

1025
00:58:26,636 --> 00:58:28,219
You have different roles, too.

1026
00:58:28,720 --> 00:58:29,714
A lawyer,

1027
00:58:30,386 --> 00:58:32,004
a daughter and a nice girlfriend.

1028
00:58:32,094 --> 00:58:33,753
Let me clarify.

1029
00:58:33,843 --> 00:58:35,672
I'm a lawyer, you're right.

1030
00:58:35,762 --> 00:58:37,796
I'm a good daughter, I guess.

1031
00:58:37,886 --> 00:58:39,843
But I don't have a boyfriend.

1032
00:58:40,344 --> 00:58:44,094
I guess you haven't gotten back
together with that Adam guy yet?

1033
00:58:45,511 --> 00:58:48,720
So he's the past,
welcome back to the market.

1034
00:58:50,136 --> 00:58:52,837
Chances of us being together
in this space and time,

1035
00:58:52,927 --> 00:58:54,171
this is destiny.

1036
00:58:54,261 --> 00:58:56,303
You want to
intrude space-time with me?

1037
00:58:57,303 --> 00:59:00,088
Are you asking your lawyer
to break the rules?

1038
00:59:00,178 --> 00:59:01,837
Life is about breaking rules

1039
00:59:01,927 --> 00:59:03,261
and knowing who you really are.

1040
00:59:04,636 --> 00:59:06,046
I'm going back tomorrow,

1041
00:59:06,136 --> 00:59:08,171
and I don't know
when I can see you again.

1042
00:59:08,261 --> 00:59:10,219
You can text me anytime.

1043
00:59:11,094 --> 00:59:13,636
This is not a good tool
for communication,

1044
00:59:14,136 --> 00:59:16,136
it's not the way
we should stay connected.

1045
00:59:16,762 --> 00:59:18,094
Then what?

1046
00:59:19,136 --> 00:59:20,886
The shadow of your smile,

1047
00:59:24,636 --> 00:59:26,094
the apple of my eye.

1048
00:59:29,136 --> 00:59:30,969
You're the sunshine of my life.

1049
00:59:35,303 --> 00:59:38,386
Perhaps you need to
break from reality.

1050
01:00:16,803 --> 01:00:20,254
Cat, please help me send
Barrister Tong's contract

1051
01:00:20,344 --> 01:00:21,762
to the Guangzhou office today.

1052
01:00:21,886 --> 01:00:22,803
Yeah.

1053
01:00:22,927 --> 01:00:23,879
Also, I won't be in
the office today.

1054
01:00:23,969 --> 01:00:25,588
Call me if anything comes up.

1055
01:00:25,678 --> 01:00:27,011
Okay, bye.

1056
01:00:52,636 --> 01:00:53,636
I have to go.

1057
01:00:54,720 --> 01:00:55,714
Bye.

1058
01:00:56,219 --> 01:00:59,678
Hey, I'll come back for you.

1059
01:01:02,053 --> 01:01:03,843
It seems like a dream,

1060
01:01:04,219 --> 01:01:06,011
we have to wake up somehow.

1061
01:01:07,053 --> 01:01:08,178
At least not now.

1062
01:01:13,178 --> 01:01:15,011
I don't want to get hurt again.

1063
01:01:15,219 --> 01:01:17,094
You won't, I promise.

1064
01:01:36,595 --> 01:01:37,589
You're here early.

1065
01:01:38,136 --> 01:01:40,344
You're early, too.
Don't you have work?

1066
01:01:44,053 --> 01:01:47,094
- What's wrong?
- Nothing.

1067
01:01:48,428 --> 01:01:50,428
Nothing? Tell me.

1068
01:01:53,843 --> 01:01:54,837
Mrs Lui.

1069
01:01:56,094 --> 01:01:58,386
We can't hide it from Eva anymore.

1070
01:02:03,136 --> 01:02:05,171
- What's wrong, mom?
- I'm fine.

1071
01:02:05,261 --> 01:02:07,843
- Tell me.
- It's nothing, really.

1072
01:02:09,261 --> 01:02:10,255
Adam.

1073
01:02:17,094 --> 01:02:21,219
We didn't tell you
because we didn't want you to worry,

1074
01:02:22,053 --> 01:02:23,636
but the doctor have just came by...

1075
01:02:26,261 --> 01:02:27,969
He confirmed that Mrs Lui has...

1076
01:02:29,219 --> 01:02:30,213
Brain cancer.

1077
01:02:38,969 --> 01:02:40,219
Can it be cured?

1078
01:02:41,219 --> 01:02:44,046
Whether it can be cured or not
and how, it doesn't matter now.

1079
01:02:44,136 --> 01:02:46,004
Everyone dies eventually, right?

1080
01:02:46,094 --> 01:02:48,136
You can't say that!

1081
01:02:49,053 --> 01:02:52,380
I'm your daughter,
how could you hide it from me?

1082
01:02:52,470 --> 01:02:55,046
You should've told me.

1083
01:02:55,136 --> 01:02:57,296
It breaks my heart when you cry,

1084
01:02:57,386 --> 01:02:58,803
so don't cry.

1085
01:03:00,595 --> 01:03:01,589
Alright.

1086
01:03:04,094 --> 01:03:06,511
- It's alright...
- How could you do that?

1087
01:03:06,636 --> 01:03:08,762
I'm fine, it'll be okay.

1088
01:03:24,303 --> 01:03:27,303
Don't be like this, it doesn't help
to be worried like this.

1089
01:03:36,094 --> 01:03:40,178
I just want my mom
to live a happy life,

1090
01:03:42,094 --> 01:03:44,470
but now she's running out of time.

1091
01:03:45,386 --> 01:03:47,672
I don't know what to do,

1092
01:03:47,762 --> 01:03:50,094
my mind's a total blank.

1093
01:03:54,094 --> 01:03:55,803
I'll go through this with you.

1094
01:03:59,136 --> 01:04:00,672
Take a leave of absence
from the firm,

1095
01:04:00,762 --> 01:04:02,969
so that you can spend some time
with your mom.

1096
01:04:13,011 --> 01:04:15,678
When my mom had cancer back then,
I met some brilliant doctors.

1097
01:04:16,136 --> 01:04:17,386
I'll contact them for you.

1098
01:04:23,011 --> 01:04:26,094
All these years,
your mom treated me like a son.

1099
01:04:26,720 --> 01:04:27,969
I'll do all I can for her.

1100
01:04:36,844 --> 01:04:37,969
Thank you.

1101
01:04:47,843 --> 01:04:49,163
Do you want me to go up with you?

1102
01:04:51,678 --> 01:04:54,004
By the way,
this is some stomach medicine.

1103
01:04:54,094 --> 01:04:56,844
Recommended by my doctor friend,
try it.

1104
01:05:16,011 --> 01:05:16,963
"Incoming call, Eva Lui"

1105
01:05:17,053 --> 01:05:20,053
- Hello?
- Hey, Eva, how's it going?

1106
01:05:21,927 --> 01:05:25,011
- Everything's okay.
- I just hope you're okay.

1107
01:05:30,136 --> 01:05:31,130
Marvel.

1108
01:05:32,720 --> 01:05:34,678
- Let's forget all these.
- Why?

1109
01:05:38,053 --> 01:05:39,178
I'm here for you.

1110
01:05:39,927 --> 01:05:43,094
I'm sorry, bye.

1111
01:05:44,969 --> 01:05:45,963
Eva?

1112
01:05:54,511 --> 01:05:57,672
"Incoming call, Ginny"

1113
01:05:57,762 --> 01:05:59,296
Marvel, good news.

1114
01:05:59,386 --> 01:06:02,553
The studio approved
the happy ending you proposed.

1115
01:06:03,303 --> 01:06:05,171
Oh, I see.

1116
01:06:05,261 --> 01:06:06,428
Thanks, Ginny.

1117
01:06:34,886 --> 01:06:36,428
Nurse!

1118
01:06:36,762 --> 01:06:37,756
Where's Lin?

1119
01:06:38,428 --> 01:06:39,421
Which Lin, sir?

1120
01:06:39,511 --> 01:06:42,837
The one who was at this bed before,
is she okay?

1121
01:06:42,927 --> 01:06:44,753
- I'm not sure.
- She came in for a dizzy spell.

1122
01:06:44,843 --> 01:06:46,588
Please, tell me where she's gone.

1123
01:06:46,678 --> 01:06:47,837
I'll help you find out.

1124
01:06:47,927 --> 01:06:49,470
I bought her an ice cream cone.

1125
01:06:49,886 --> 01:06:50,754
Please.

1126
01:06:50,844 --> 01:06:52,046
- I'll check for you.
- Is she okay?

1127
01:06:52,136 --> 01:06:55,011
"Saint Teresa's Hospital"

1128
01:06:56,011 --> 01:06:57,969
I told you to stop crying,

1129
01:06:58,344 --> 01:06:59,546
You're so pretty when you smile.

1130
01:06:59,636 --> 01:07:00,844
So smile for me, will you?

1131
01:07:13,927 --> 01:07:17,380
"Po-wah"

1132
01:07:17,470 --> 01:07:19,553
"27 missed calls from Po-wah"

1133
01:07:24,428 --> 01:07:25,713
Oh, the poor thing.

1134
01:07:25,803 --> 01:07:26,843
It can't get that off.

1135
01:07:27,053 --> 01:07:28,762
And it can't even walk now!

1136
01:07:29,303 --> 01:07:31,511
It's just too stupid
to be cute, right?

1137
01:07:32,553 --> 01:07:34,505
"Po-wah"

1138
01:07:34,595 --> 01:07:36,921
"I'm worried about you,
you won't answer..."

1139
01:07:37,011 --> 01:07:39,261
"Do you want to delete your
conversation with Po-wah?"

1140
01:07:42,386 --> 01:07:43,386
"Delete"

1141
01:07:44,886 --> 01:07:47,296
All my life,

1142
01:07:47,386 --> 01:07:50,421
I've only done
whatever people want me to do.

1143
01:07:50,511 --> 01:07:54,636
Can I finally
call the shots this time?

1144
01:07:58,762 --> 01:08:03,094
I don't want to keep
switching hospitals,

1145
01:08:04,053 --> 01:08:08,261
nor keep switching doctors anymore.

1146
01:08:10,178 --> 01:08:11,261
I'm in pain.

1147
01:08:13,011 --> 01:08:14,303
This is torture.

1148
01:08:37,303 --> 01:08:38,297
Eva.

1149
01:08:42,636 --> 01:08:44,762
- This is for you.
- Really?

1150
01:08:47,303 --> 01:08:48,470
This is beautiful.

1151
01:08:51,094 --> 01:08:52,672
It'll take forever
to fold all of these.

1152
01:08:52,762 --> 01:08:53,630
"He broke his leg,
he needs a cast..."

1153
01:08:53,720 --> 01:08:55,630
It's not that many,
just 3,000 of them.

1154
01:08:55,720 --> 01:08:59,011
- 3,000?
- We'll fold it together.

1155
01:09:00,094 --> 01:09:01,803
You can even write on them.

1156
01:09:03,844 --> 01:09:05,844
Let me see what you wrote.

1157
01:09:06,219 --> 01:09:11,171
"I felt a shock the first time
we held hands, as the legends say!"

1158
01:09:11,261 --> 01:09:14,505
"On our first trip,
he forgot his passport!"

1159
01:09:14,595 --> 01:09:17,713
"He got his driver's license
for the first time!"

1160
01:09:17,803 --> 01:09:19,428
Say, did you receive
my text message?

1161
01:09:19,762 --> 01:09:20,762
What message?

1162
01:09:26,844 --> 01:09:29,927
I don't know what I can do to
make you forgive me the 78th time,

1163
01:09:31,803 --> 01:09:34,344
but if you do give me
one more chance,

1164
01:09:35,762 --> 01:09:37,219
I won't let you down.

1165
01:09:44,843 --> 01:09:46,203
I have the same dream every night,

1166
01:09:46,886 --> 01:09:50,261
that my daughter
would have a romantic wedding.

1167
01:09:54,803 --> 01:09:57,011
Will you make
that dream come true for me?

1168
01:10:00,678 --> 01:10:02,380
Go ahead and have another dream.

1169
01:10:02,470 --> 01:10:03,963
- Come on, hurry up!
- You naughty girl!

1170
01:10:04,053 --> 01:10:05,493
- Alright, go have your dream.
- Hey!

1171
01:10:08,886 --> 01:10:11,672
- Are you okay?
- Can you give me a hand?

1172
01:10:11,762 --> 01:10:12,803
I'm coming in, then.

1173
01:10:26,969 --> 01:10:27,963
It's gorgeous.

1174
01:10:31,886 --> 01:10:32,880
Adam.

1175
01:10:34,178 --> 01:10:37,261
Did you know that one out of
five marriages end in divorce?

1176
01:10:40,720 --> 01:10:42,219
My parents are one of them.

1177
01:10:44,011 --> 01:10:46,004
I don't mean to force you,

1178
01:10:46,094 --> 01:10:47,213
I don't want you to do this
because my mom...

1179
01:10:47,303 --> 01:10:48,969
I want to do this.

1180
01:10:52,219 --> 01:10:54,129
After our breakup,

1181
01:10:54,219 --> 01:10:57,254
I thought that maybe

1182
01:10:57,344 --> 01:11:01,004
I had too many impractical fantasies
and expectations for you.

1183
01:11:01,094 --> 01:11:02,296
Maybe I read too many fairy tales

1184
01:11:02,386 --> 01:11:04,470
with princes and princesses,

1185
01:11:06,843 --> 01:11:08,927
maybe I should be more like
the people around me.

1186
01:11:09,803 --> 01:11:13,094
As well as lower my expectations,
so that I wouldn't be disappointed.

1187
01:11:13,678 --> 01:11:14,843
You don't have to do that.

1188
01:11:16,386 --> 01:11:19,762
If you feel uncomfortable
after the wedding,

1189
01:11:21,386 --> 01:11:22,844
you can choose all over again.

1190
01:11:24,803 --> 01:11:27,178
Fulfilling your mom's wish
is the most important thing now.

1191
01:11:36,094 --> 01:11:37,796
Okay, look at this way.

1192
01:11:37,886 --> 01:11:40,511
Look at each other now, good.

1193
01:11:42,219 --> 01:11:43,171
Another one.

1194
01:11:43,261 --> 01:11:45,886
One, two, three.

1195
01:11:55,886 --> 01:11:57,178
One, two, three.

1196
01:12:00,011 --> 01:12:01,386
Too many red balloons!

1197
01:12:03,136 --> 01:12:04,261
One, two and swing!

1198
01:12:24,843 --> 01:12:26,136
Isn't it adorable?

1199
01:12:26,969 --> 01:12:29,303
- You two look great together!
- Look at this.

1200
01:12:29,636 --> 01:12:31,261
You're really great together!

1201
01:12:32,219 --> 01:12:33,553
The perfect match!

1202
01:12:37,803 --> 01:12:39,969
Honey, that's a beautiful dress!

1203
01:12:41,969 --> 01:12:43,428
Doesn't my daughter look pretty?

1204
01:12:45,470 --> 01:12:46,421
"Eva and Adam's Wedding"

1205
01:12:46,511 --> 01:12:54,254
"Marriage is between two people,"

1206
01:12:54,344 --> 01:13:01,380
"but a wedding involves
the whole world."

1207
01:13:01,470 --> 01:13:09,254
The bridal car's okay,
fast and furious!

1208
01:13:09,344 --> 01:13:13,963
"Flower shop is okay."

1209
01:13:14,053 --> 01:13:16,546
"Make-up is okay."

1210
01:13:16,636 --> 01:13:24,753
"The wedding venue is set."

1211
01:13:24,843 --> 01:13:28,136
Please give me a job, period.

1212
01:13:29,178 --> 01:13:31,511
Except for arranging seating.

1213
01:13:32,844 --> 01:13:36,296
"How's this backdrop?"

1214
01:13:36,386 --> 01:13:39,843
"Discount from my friend,"

1215
01:13:40,219 --> 01:13:43,588
"35 percent off."

1216
01:13:43,678 --> 01:13:46,630
I say again, period.

1217
01:13:46,720 --> 01:13:50,720
Don't force me to wear that
bridesmaid dress, exclamation mark.

1218
01:13:53,720 --> 01:13:58,844
"Love you all."

1219
01:14:07,303 --> 01:14:08,297
Excuse me.

1220
01:14:14,969 --> 01:14:16,927
I'm flying
out on working holiday tomorrow.

1221
01:14:17,178 --> 01:14:19,886
Come out for a drink
with me tonight, send me off.

1222
01:14:21,136 --> 01:14:22,595
I'm getting married in a few days.

1223
01:14:26,927 --> 01:14:27,921
Oh, to Eva?

1224
01:14:28,720 --> 01:14:29,714
Yeah.

1225
01:14:31,428 --> 01:14:32,948
You've got better taste
than her, then.

1226
01:14:35,470 --> 01:14:36,464
Anyway,

1227
01:14:38,094 --> 01:14:40,088
thanks for sending the link

1228
01:14:40,178 --> 01:14:41,470
of that "77 Heartwarmings".

1229
01:14:43,094 --> 01:14:45,678
I didn't do it, why would I do that?

1230
01:14:46,927 --> 01:14:47,969
It wasn't you?

1231
01:14:48,844 --> 01:14:50,344
Have a good marriage.

1232
01:14:50,720 --> 01:14:52,762
If you get divorced, call me.

1233
01:15:32,011 --> 01:15:33,011
Here you are.

1234
01:15:35,720 --> 01:15:37,844
- Your fan letters.
- Thanks.

1235
01:15:40,011 --> 01:15:41,178
It's so cute.

1236
01:15:41,386 --> 01:15:43,843
- Drink mine.
- Thank you.

1237
01:15:47,094 --> 01:15:48,636
Back here for filming?

1238
01:15:48,844 --> 01:15:52,053
I hope it's not for
another Space-time Intrusion.

1239
01:15:52,261 --> 01:15:53,511
I came back for you.

1240
01:15:56,511 --> 01:16:00,386
Marvel, my wedding
is in a couple of days.

1241
01:16:01,011 --> 01:16:02,136
So...

1242
01:16:03,844 --> 01:16:06,386
You decided to give the audience
a happy ending?

1243
01:16:07,011 --> 01:16:08,386
As you said,

1244
01:16:08,678 --> 01:16:10,296
life is about breaking the rules

1245
01:16:10,386 --> 01:16:12,219
to find who you really are.

1246
01:16:14,178 --> 01:16:16,921
Which means life and love
are conflicting.

1247
01:16:17,011 --> 01:16:19,011
Every movie has an ending.

1248
01:16:19,261 --> 01:16:20,837
But why does it end here?

1249
01:16:20,927 --> 01:16:22,470
The audiences.

1250
01:16:25,219 --> 01:16:26,886
The wedding's not only for me.

1251
01:16:28,344 --> 01:16:30,053
Your case is closed.

1252
01:16:33,678 --> 01:16:34,886
If I were you,

1253
01:16:36,303 --> 01:16:37,886
I would change the ending.

1254
01:16:39,969 --> 01:16:41,886
But I'm just a simple girl,

1255
01:16:43,511 --> 01:16:46,178
not a Space-time Intruder.

1256
01:17:19,511 --> 01:17:20,511
Thank you.

1257
01:17:22,843 --> 01:17:24,428
Mrs Lui, wait here.

1258
01:17:50,844 --> 01:17:52,178
You look beautiful today.

1259
01:17:53,762 --> 01:17:54,921
What are they doing?

1260
01:17:55,011 --> 01:17:57,636
Adam and I have a surprise for you.

1261
01:18:07,886 --> 01:18:10,843
That's your mother.

1262
01:18:12,720 --> 01:18:15,678
Look at this one,
she is so beautiful!

1263
01:18:31,053 --> 01:18:32,053
This is for you.

1264
01:18:34,011 --> 01:18:35,005
Thank you.

1265
01:18:38,344 --> 01:18:40,428
We've lost a lot of time.

1266
01:18:40,553 --> 01:18:41,380
Therefore, today,

1267
01:18:41,470 --> 01:18:43,338
in front of
your daughter and Adam...

1268
01:18:43,428 --> 01:18:44,843
I'd like to ask...

1269
01:18:46,803 --> 01:18:48,136
Will you marry me?

1270
01:18:58,053 --> 01:18:59,303
I do.

1271
01:19:14,136 --> 01:19:16,886
I've picked a dress for you, Mom.

1272
01:19:33,011 --> 01:19:34,005
Look.

1273
01:19:37,344 --> 01:19:42,219
This dress looks like
the wedding dress in my dream.

1274
01:19:44,969 --> 01:19:46,803
You'll look beautiful in it.

1275
01:19:49,803 --> 01:19:50,927
Thank you.

1276
01:19:54,678 --> 01:19:56,421
Thank you all for attending...

1277
01:19:56,511 --> 01:19:58,837
Wait, don't get married!

1278
01:19:58,927 --> 01:20:00,254
Stop the execution!

1279
01:20:00,344 --> 01:20:01,338
You again?

1280
01:20:03,344 --> 01:20:04,428
Don't mess things up here.

1281
01:20:04,886 --> 01:20:06,754
- You look familiar.
- Last time...

1282
01:20:06,844 --> 01:20:10,386
I'm not getting married,
so just sit down and be the VIP!

1283
01:20:11,927 --> 01:20:13,678
Eva's mother is getting married.

1284
01:20:14,053 --> 01:20:15,933
- Have a seat.
- Congratulations, Mother-in-law.

1285
01:20:17,178 --> 01:20:18,172
What mother-in-law?

1286
01:20:19,011 --> 01:20:19,886
Not true!

1287
01:20:20,094 --> 01:20:21,886
Let's start.

1288
01:20:22,511 --> 01:20:24,546
Thank you for attending

1289
01:20:24,636 --> 01:20:27,511
Mei-lin and Po-wah's wedding today.

1290
01:20:33,969 --> 01:20:36,803
This is Lin,
she doesn't have many hobbies.

1291
01:20:36,927 --> 01:20:40,219
Her only hobby
is taking care of her daughter,

1292
01:20:40,886 --> 01:20:43,803
but she's never asked her daughter
to take care of her.

1293
01:20:44,511 --> 01:20:47,296
Women in her generation
never asked for much.

1294
01:20:47,386 --> 01:20:51,588
As long as their families stay
together and stay happy,

1295
01:20:51,678 --> 01:20:53,386
they'll feel content.

1296
01:20:53,969 --> 01:20:56,713
All these years,
Lin's responsibilities

1297
01:20:56,803 --> 01:20:59,470
outweighed her own happiness.

1298
01:20:59,969 --> 01:21:02,386
Lin didn't ask for this,

